%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20widespread%20election%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%202020%20election.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20Hutchinson%20said%20she%20came%20into%20a%20room%20after%20the%20president%20and%20witnessed%20%26quot%3Bketchup%20dripping%20down%20the%20wall%20and%20there%20was%20a%20shattered%20porcelain%20plate%20on%20the%20floor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it%20would%20happen%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20week%2C%20sometimes%20more.%20Sometimes%20there'd%20be%20a%20week%20or%20so%20lull%2C%20but%20then%20there%20would%20be%20a%20bad%20news%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20Hutchinson%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-would-often-throw-food-against-wall-cassidy-hutchinson-2023-10%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTrump%2520would%2520throw%2520food%2520against%2CHouse%2520aide%2520Cassidy%2520Hutchinson%2520says%26amp%3Btext%3DCassidy%2520Hutchinson%2520said%2520Trump%2520used%2Cwould%2520sometimes%2520flip%2520the%2520tablecloth.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BJimmy%20Kimmel%20Live!%26quot%3B%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20October%2C%20referring%20to%20Trump's%20chucking%20habits.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20wasn't%20just%20launching%20the%20food%20and%20the%20plates%20and%20the%20porcelain%20at%20the%20wall.%20It%20was%20sometimes%20just%20flipping%20the%20tablecloth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20podcast%20appearance%2C%20Kaplan%20also%20said%20once%20the%20deposition%20ended%2C%20Trump%20dismissed%20her%20%E2%80%94%20off%20the%20record%20%E2%80%94%20by%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BSee%20you%20next%20Tuesday%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20euphemism%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20a%20derogatory%20word%20indicating%20female%20genitalia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20said%20she%20was%20confused%20because%20she%20and%20Trump%20were%20supposed%20to%20meet%20on%20a%20Wednesday.%20She%20said%20she%20didn't%20learn%20what%20it%20meant%20until%20after%20she%20left%20and%20her%20team%20infor