m-govt-spent-over-rs-108-cr-as-rent-for-choppers-aircraft-in-5-years-minister%2F1759119%2F%5C%22%3Ehired%20chartered%20planes%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20taxpayers%E2%80%99%20money%20to%20attend%20a%20number%20of%20weddings%2C%20apart%20from%20party%20meetings.%20No%20government%20is%20supposed%20to%20spend%20any%20public%20funds%20on%20non-official%20work.%20%E2%80%98Non-official%20work%E2%80%99%20naturally%20includes%20party-related%20activities%20and%20attending%20private%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20neither%20of%20which%20can%20be%20paid%20for%20by%20public%20funds.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20September%2C%20the%20Sarma%20government%20had%20claimed%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20that%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20hiring%20chartered%20planes%20were%20only%20for%20government%20programmes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInitially%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20General%20Administration%20Department%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20the%20RTI%20application%20filed%20in%20August%202022%2C%20seeking%20information%20on%20such%20financial%20overheads%20of%20the%20government.%20On%20September%2030%2C%202023%2C%20Pradip%20Sarma%2C%20under%20secretary%20and%20State%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20at%20the%20department%2C%20shared%20some%20information%20only%20after%20the%20State%20Information%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20responding%20to%20The%20CrossCurrent%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20%E2%80%93%20directed%20it%20to%20do%20so%20on%20August%208%2C%202023.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20RTI%20application%20had%20sought%20such%20details%20from%20May%2010%2C%202021%2C%20till%20the%20time%20of%20reply%2C%20the%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20department%20even%20after%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20direction%2C%20has%20only%20been%20partial.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20reporters%20filed%20a%20separate%20RTI%20request%20with%20the%20Assam%20Tourism%20Development%20Corporation%20(ATDC)%2C%20related%20to%20the%20department%20hiring%20chartered%20flights%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20use%20as%20such%20services%20are%20routed%20through%20ATDC%20by%20the%20state%20administration.%20The%20ATDC%20is%20yet%20to%20reply%2C%20even%20though%20three%20months%20have%20passed.%20This%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%202005%20which%20says%20the%20officers%20designated%20as%20the%20first%20appellate%20authority%20must%20reply%20to%20an%20RTI%20query%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcic.gov.in%2Fcomplaint-guidelines%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewithin%2030%20days%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20model%20conduct%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fmcc%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eclause%207%20(a)%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20ministers%20shall%20not%20combine%20their%20official%20visit%20with%20electioneering%20work%20and%20shall%20not%20also%20make%20use%20of%20official%20machinery%20or%20personnel%20during%20the%20electioneering%20work.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClause%207%20(b)%20explicitly%20states%20that%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20transport%20including%20official%20aircrafts%2C%20vehicles%2C%20machinery%20and%20personnel%20shall%20not%20be%20used%20for%20furtherance%20of%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20party%20in%20power.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20government-provided%20information%2C%20though%20partial%2C%20and%20photographic%20evidence%20from%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20own%20social%20media%20handles%20have%20shown%20that%20the%20chief%20minister%20violated%20the%20code%20at%20least%20five%20times%2C%20by%20using%20Assam%20government%20funded%20helicopters%20to%20campaign%20for%20the%20candidates%20of%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20allies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%