0uttered%20two%20words%20I%20did%20not%20understand%3A%20%E2%80%9CPuriya%20Dhanashree%E2%80%9D.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20that%20meant.%20He%20told%20me%20it%20was%20the%20name%20of%20an%20evening%20raga%2C%20belonging%20to%20the%20Purvi%20that%2C%20and%20the%20song%20had%20been%20composed%20in%20that%20raga.%20None%20of%20that%20made%20much%20sense%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20words%20%E2%80%9CPuriya%20Dhanashree%E2%80%9D%2C%20however%2C%20I%20memorized.%20Or%20did%20I%20note%20them%20down%3F%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20recall%20now.%20But%20there%20was%20something%20about%20that%20melody%2C%20something%20about%20these%20strange%20sounding%20words%2C%20and%20something%20about%20that%20morning%2C%20which%20left%20me%20in%20a%20dreamlike%20valley%20with%20an%20everlasting%20evening.%20I%20had%20found%20the%20song.%20But%20the%20mystery%2C%20I%20was%20told%2C%20had%20a%20deeper%2C%20an%20older%20source.%20I%20could%20not%20wait%20to%20explore%20this%20new%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20quench%20my%20thirst%20for%20what%20I%20had%20recently%20discovered%2C%20I%20checked%20a%20few%20of%20Lahore%E2%80%99s%20music%20stores%20within%20my%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20transitioning%20from%20cassettes%20to%20CDs%20%E2%80%94%20but%20no%20one%20had%20any%20idea%20about%20what%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%20Everything%20was%20changing%20fast.%20It%20seemed%20everyone%20wanted%20to%20speed%20up%20to%20match%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20new%20millennium.%20Like%20any%20millennial%2C%20I%20had%20witnessed%20the%20transformation%20from%20audiocassettes%20to%20CDs%20and%20MP3%20players%20to%20IPods%2C%20just%20in%20a%20few%20years.%20And%20here%20I%20was%2C%20an%20early%20teenager%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20something%20with%20ancient%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20later%2C%20when%20we%20went%20to%20a%20newly%20constructed%20shopping%20mall%2C%20I%20finally%20found%20a%20CD%20at%20a%20big%20music%20store%20%E2%80%93%