nformal%20sector.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20feeble%20measures%20to%20provide%20easy%20loans%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98startups%E2%80%99%20belittles%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20unemployment%20and%20underemployment%20crisis%20facing%20the%20country.%20Nor%20does%20it%20address%20the%20question%20of%20lack%20of%20labour%20protections%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98gig%20economy%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20a%20number%20of%20young%20people%20work%20on%20meagre%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20schemes%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%20speaks%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esabka%20saath%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20approach%2C%20but%20allocates%20grossly%20insufficient%20amounts%20to%20key%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Social%20Assistance%20Programme%20(NSAP)%20witnesses%20a%20meagre%2016%20crore%20increase%2C%20with%20the%20budget%20inching%20up%20from%20Rs%209%2C636%20crore%20(BE%202023-2024)%20to%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2FBudget_at_Glance%2Fbudget_at_a_glance.pdf%5C%22%3E9%2C652%20crore%20(BE%202024-2025)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20last%20revision%20in%20the%20amount%20disbursed%20per%20individual%20happened%20in%202007%2C%20and%2016%20years%20later%2C%20it%20still%20stands%20at%20Rs%20200%20crore.%20Even%20a%20simple%20inflation%20adjustment%20has%20not%20been%20done%20to%20this%20paltry%20sum%2C%20which%20would%20have%20amounted%20to%20Rs%20618.09%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(NREGA)%20allocation%20shows%20no%20increase%2C%20remaining%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2FBudget_at_Glance%2Fbudget_at_a_glance.pdf%5C%22%3ERs%2086%2C000%20crores%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BE%202024-2025)%2C%20which%20was%20the%20revised%20estimate%20for%20the%20year%202023-2024%2C%20initially%20estimated%20at%20a%20low%20of%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore.%20On%20top%20of%20that%20onl