le-east%2Fisrael-pm-netanyahu-slams-us-president-bidens-condemnation-of-israeli-settlers%2Famp_articleshow%2F107374456.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20Professor%20JPS%3A%20The%20Teacher%20One%20Never%20Had%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02153824%2Fad379b3d-0f6a-4ff0-8f8d-5962e7b32ec2.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%5BO%5Dbviously%20there%20is%20no%20classification%20of%20the%20universe%20that%20is%20not%20arbitrary%20and%20conjectural.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%E2%88%BC%20Jorge%20Luis%20Borges%2C%201952%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%5BE%5Dveryting%20swarajist%20is%20good%20for%20swadeshi%2C%20but%20everything%20swadeshi%20is%20not%20good%20for%20swaraj.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%E2%88%BC%20Jit%20Pal%20Singh%20Uberoi%2C%201974%2C%20as%20indebted%20to%20K.J.%20Shah%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20I%20prepare%20to%20disengage%2C%20formally%2C%20from%20academia%2C%20I%20am%20always%20gripped%20by%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20foreboding%2C%20not%20quite%20of%20my%20own%20finitude%2C%20but%20necessarily%20of%20my%20teachers%20(and%20mentors)%20passing%20away.%20Many%20have%20passed%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%3B%20and%20even%20as%20I%20have%20brooded%2C%20I%20have%20not%20let%20the%20emotions%20take%20over.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20somewhat%20surprising%20%E2%80%93%20to%20me%20at%20least%20%E2%80%93%20that%20I%20should%20be%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20passing%20away%20of%20Professor%20Jit%20Pal%20Singh%20Uberoi%20(JPS%2C%20for%20short).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJPS%20was%20never%20quite%20my%20formal%20teacher%2C%20nor%20did%20I%20seek%20out%20his%20mentorship%3B%20in%20fact%2C%20there%20were%20only%20a%20few%20times%20that%20our%20paths%20crossed%2C%20although%20each%20moment%20of%20that%20crossing%20was%20quite%20intense%20and%20memorable.%20I%20have%20always%20cherished%20them%2C%20and%20hopefully%20this%20point%20will%20come%20through%20in%20this%20remembrance.%20Of%20course%2C%20I%20have%20been%20a%20fervent%20reader%20of%20all%20that%20he%20wrote%20%E2%80%93%20and%20there%20is%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20a%20corpus%20to%20be%20absorbed%20and%20engaged%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20has%20been%20quite%20formative%20of%20my%20own%20commitments%20and%20preoccupations%2C%20scholarly%20and%20otherwise.%20This%20latter%20point%20could%20go%20some%20way%20in%20clarifying%20what%20I%20have%20summarised%20in%20my%20title%20as%20%E2%80%98Remembering%20Prof%20JPS%3A%20The%20Teacher%20One%20Never%20Had%E2%80%99.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20therefore%2C%20in%20accounting%20for%20JPS%20and%20the%20fields%20of%20his%20thought%2C%20I%20am%20also%20framing%20for%20myself%20the%20passage%20of%20my%20own%20thought%20and%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20is%20about%20JPS%20and%20not%20about%20myself%20%E2%80%93%20although%2C%20yes%2C%20in%20foregrounding%20the%20thoughts%20that%20I%20will%2C%20the%20effort%20is%20to%20communicate%20a%20sense%20of%20his%20passing%20(as%20much%20for%20myself%2C%20as%20for%20my%20younger%20colleagues%20and%20students%20at%20large).%20JPS%20spoke%20of%20his%20research%20and%20pedagogy%20as%20following%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnon-dualist%20or%20dialectical%20semiology%E2%80%9D%2C%20retraceable%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CHermetic%20tradition%20in%20modern%20times%2C%20say%2C%20from%20Paracelsus%20to%20Goethe%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98non-dualism%E2%80%99%20translating%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20something%20like%20%3Cem%3Eadvaita%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Sanskrit%2C%20but%20more%20akin%20to%20%3Cem%3Enirdvandva%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20non-acceptance%20of%20the%20two%20principles%2C%20for%20example%2C%20of%20the%20subject%20and%20the%20object%20or%20of%20self%20and%20the%20world%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%202019).%20Forever%20the%20%E2%80%98complacent%20disciplinarian%E2%80%99%20(I%20draw%20this%20term%20from%20Ian%20Hacking)%2C%20JPS%20brought%20to%20the%20discipline%20of%20sociology%20and%20social%20anthropology%20in%20India%20a%20style%20of%20thinking%20that%20rejected%20%E2%80%98monism%20and%20dualism%E2%80%99%20and%20veered%20towards%20(in%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20own%20words)%20%E2%80%9Csome%20form%20of%20Trinitarian%20doctrine%2C%20such%20as%20types%20of%20opposition%20and%20mediation%2C%20or%20a%20dialectic%20of%20thesis%2C%20antithesis%20and%20synthesis%2C%20followed%20by%20reflection%2C%20elaboration%20and%20completion%20or%20reproduction%2C%20or%20the%20set%20of%20equality%2C%20polarity%20and%20progression%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%202019).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELest%20all%20this%20seem%20a%20mishmash%20of%20orientations%20and%20even%20philosophically%20obscure%2C%20I%20must%20reiterate%20that%20the%20emergent%20spheres%20of%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20work%20were%20always%20marked%20by%20a%20precise%20%E2%80%9Cinterplay%20of%20method%2C%20theory%20and%20data%E2%80%9D.%20Hopefully%2C%20the%20elucidation%20that%20follows%20will%20substantiate%20this%20rendition%2C%20even%20as%20I%20go%20on%20to%20complicate%20the%20philosophy%20and%20sociology%20on%20offer.%C2%A0%20Given%20the%20circumstances%2C%20yet%2C%20I%20will%20have%20to%20be%20brief%2C%20often%20giving%20the%20space%20over%20to%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20own%20prose%2C%20even%20as%20a%20fuller%20formulation%20at%20my%20own%20end%20is%20on%20the%20anvil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisciplinary%20trysts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20JPS%20encodes%20the%20possibilities%20summarily%20reproduced%20in%20my%20lines%20above%20from%20Jorge%20Luis%20Borges.%C2%A0%20The%20context%20of%20those%20lines%20need%20not%20absorb%20us%20here%2C%20but%20given%20the%20salience%20of%20questions%20of%20form%20and%20symbolism%20that%20comprises%20key%20aspects%20of%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20they%20reproduce%20in%20good%20measure%20the%20%E2%80%98imagination%E2%80%99%20that%20governs%20his%20overall%20corpus.%20The%20anthology%20of%20his%20writings%2C%20compiled%20and%20edited%20by%20Khalid%20Tyabji%2C%20with%20the%20title%20%3Cem%3EMind%20and%20Society%3A%20From%20Indian%20Studies%20to%20General%20Sociology%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Oxford%20University%20Press%2C%202019)%20does%20give%20us%20a%20sense%20of%20his%20work%20%E2%80%93%20their%20shifting%20tides%2C%20the%20various%20styles%20of%20thinking%20that%20JPS%20arraigned%20against%20and%20the%20traditions%20of%20thought%20he%20sought%20to%20promote%2C%20and%20the%20nuanced%20formalism%20of%20his%20ways%2C%20at%20once%20non-arbitrary%20and%20conjectural%20in%20a%20deep%20kind%20of%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Preface%E2%80%99%20to%20this%20compilation%20recalls%20summarily%2C%20in%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20own%20words%2C%20his%20trajectory%20through%20physical%20science%20and%20technology%20(even%20graduating%20from%20University%20College%20London%20in%20electrical%20engineering%2Ftelecommunications%2C%201952-55)%20and%20drifting%20into%20social%20science%20in%20the%20sway%20and%20friendship%20of%20the%20redoubtable%20Basil%20Bernstein%20(who%20directed%20JPS%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20and%20the%20School%20of%20Social%20Anthropology%20thereon%2C%201955-58).%20Following%20a%20teaching%20stint%20at%20Monash%20University%20in%20Melbourne%2C%20Australia%20(1963-66)%2C%20JPS%20moved%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20at%20Delhi%20School%20of%20Economics%20(DSE)%20in%201968%20and%20remained%20therein%20until%20his%20retirement%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Preface%E2%80%99%20also%20constructs%20the%20three%20thematic%20configurations%20of%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98general%20sociology%E2%80%99%3A%20one%20having%20to%20do%20with%20(as%20he%20puts%20it)%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20eternal%20political%20war%20of%20imperialism%20versus%20nationalism%2C%20as%20it%20related%20to%20the%20academic%20pursuit%20of%20knowledge%20in%20the%20university%20and%20the%20profession%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20other%20with%20%E2%80%9Ccritical%20reflections%20on%20aspects%20of%20modern%20Western%20mentality%2C%20whether%20academic%20or%20theoretical%20and%20practical%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20third%20laying%20bare%20the%20%E2%80%9Coriginal%20project%20of%20a%20vernacular%20Indian%20modernity%2C%E2%80%9D%20whose%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20%E2%80%98principle%20of%20motion%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20is%20located%20in%20society%20rather%20than%20the%20state%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%202019).%20As%20he%20retrospectively%20renders%20the%20terms%20of%20his%20quest%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20overall%20idea%20is%20to%20find%20the%20ground%20for%20a%20concept%20of%20%3Cem%3Esociety%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20vernacular%20usage%2C%20labour%2C%20or%20language%2C%20rather%20than%20in%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98tradition%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20general%20social%20science%20and%20the%20Orientalist%20classicists%20had%20hitherto%20assumed%E2%80%9D%20(2019).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20this%20last%20axis%20also%20meant%20a%20negotiation%20of%20the%20space%20of%20religions%20in%20India%20and%20Sikhism%20in%20particular%20(see%20his%20ambitiously%20mounted%2C%20and%20yet%20impossibly%20arcane%2C%20mode%20of%20analysis%20in%20%3Cem%3EReligion%2C%20Civil%20Society%20and%20the%20State%3A%20A%20Study%20of%20Sikhism%3C%2Fem%3E%20(OUP%2C%201996))%20and%20the%20stunning%20thought%20anchoring%20the%20same%2C%20namely%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndianness%20of%20India%2C%20from%20a%20national%2C%20structural%20or%20relational%20view%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bwould%20still%20require%5D%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20problem%20of%20the%20relation%20of%20self%20and%20other%2C%20or%20rather%20of%20self%20and%20the%20other%20self%20%E2%80%A6%20to%20be%20addressed%E2%80%9D%20at%20both%20the%20individual%20and%20collective%20levels.%C2%A0%20As%20such%2C%20the%20work%20was%20sweeping%20in%20its%20stakes%2C%20even%20mounting%20a%20%E2%80%98structural%E2%80%99%20parallel%20between%20Sikhism%20and%20%E2%80%9CGandhism%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20early%2020th%C2%A0century%20(1920-25)%2C%20whilst%20also%20insisting%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cproblem%20of%20religion%2C%20politics%20and%20history%20or%20of%20their%20inter-relation%20is%20always%20in%20the%20background%20of%20the%20mind%20of%20all%20writers%20on%20Sikhism%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20the%20specific%20project%20or%20ambition%20of%20Sikhism%20to%20bring%20the%20three%20spheres%20of%20religion%2C%20the%20state%20and%20society%20together%2C%20face%20to%20face%E2%80%9D%20(even%20as%20%E2%80%9Cin%20medieval%20India%20the%20three%20were%20situated%20back%20to%20back%2C%20walled%20off%20from%20each%20other%2C%20either%20for%20safety%E2%80%99s%20sake%20or%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20principle%E2%80%9D)%20%5BJPS%2C%201996%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20his%20critics%20have%20noted%20that%20the%20work%20cut%20many%20historical%20and%20methodological%20corners%2C%20there%20is%20no%20denying%20the%20mystique%20of%20its%20central%20thesis%20working%20off%20Sikhism%20%E2%80%93%20away%20from%20all%20frameworks%20of%20the%20majority%20and%20the%20minority%2C%20the%20mainstream%20and%20the%20margin%2C%20or%20even%20homogeneity%20and%20heterogeneity%20%E2%80%93%20and%20foregrounding%20the%20%E2%80%98martyr%E2%80%99%20as%20a%20figure%20of%20victory%20over%20the%20%E2%80%98%E2%80%99self%E2%80%99%20(as%20distinct%20from%20the%20figure%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%20or%20the%20victim%20as%20command%20over%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99).%C2%A0%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20claim%20here%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmartyrdom%20as%20a%20creed%20(%3Cem%3Eshahadat%3C%2Fem%3E)%20is%20more%20or%20less%20equivalent%20to%20non-violence%20as%20a%20creed%20(%3Cem%3Esatyagraha%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20the%20making%20of%20Indian%20modernity%20from%20the%20birth%20of%20Sikhism%20up%20to%20Gandhism%E2%80%9D%20needs%20some%20unpacking%20and%20further%20contextual%20commentary.%C2%A0%20But%20that%20was%20JPS%2C%20flirting%20paradoxically%20with%20the%20very%20heroic%20that%20he%20was%20striving%20to%20displace%20as%20the%20central%20figure%20of%20culture%20and%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20any%20rate%2C%20my%20own%20tryst%20with%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20writings%20began%20with%20his%20two%20essays%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EContributions%20to%20Indian%20Sociology%3C%2Fem%3E%20(N.S.)%2C%20both%20subsumed%20under%20the%20rubric%20of%20%E2%80%98For%20a%20Sociology%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%99%20one%20titled%20%E2%80%98Science%20and%20Swaraj%E2%80%99%20(1968)%20and%20the%20other%20titled%20%E2%80%98New%20Outlines%20of%20Structural%20Sociology%2C%201945-1970%E2%80%99%20(1974).%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20latter%20essay%20was%20building%20on%20the%20impetus%20of%20the%20former%20%E2%80%93%20specifically%20the%20claim%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20%3Cem%3Elife%20of%20mind%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20group%20affair%20as%20well%20as%20an%20individual%20affair%2C%20so%20that%20our%20object%20should%20be%20to%20strengthen%20the%20%3Cem%3Einstitutional%20sinews%20of%20national%20intellectual%20life%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20well%20as%20to%20improve%20its%20%3Cem%3Equality%20and%20relevance%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(emphasis%20added)%20%E2%80%93%20even%20as%20it%20sought%20to%20forge%20a%20%E2%80%9Cresearch%20plan%20for%20work%20on%20%3Cem%3Estructural%20sociology%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(emphasis%20in%20original)%20based%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cswarajist%20attitude%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%201974).%20The%20detailing%20offered%20in%20this%20relatively%20long%20essay%20need%20not%20concern%20us%20here%2C%20but%20the%20intent%20to%20evaluate%20the%20%E2%80%9Cchallenge%20of%20structuralism%20to%20the%20social%20and%20human%20sciences%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20must%20be%20emphasised.%20Indeed%2C%20working%20off%20the%20conviction%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20will%20not%20do%20borrow%2C%20adapt%2C%20and%20apply%20ideas%20to%20India%2C%20unless%20the%20ideas%20are%20effectively%20reconstructed%20in%20the%20process%20by%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20JPS%20actively%20sought%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpresent%20structuralism%2C%20less%20as%20a%20set%20method%20of%20universal%20validity%2C%20and%20more%20as%20a%20family%20or%20cognate%20group%20of%20theories%20in%20fields%20considered%20to%20be%20of%20interest%20to%20us%E2%80%9D%20(1974).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20own%20spheres%20of%20work%2C%20traversing%20the%20contours%20of%20sociological%20scholarship%20in%20India%2C%20I%20found%20this%20essay%20particularly%20insightful%20in%20laying%20bare%20the%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20truly%20comparative%20sociology%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20set%20apart%20from%20the%20extant%20and%20pervasive%20%E2%80%9Ctypological%20classification%20of%20societies%2C%20e.g.%20industrial%2C%20agrarian%20and%20tribal%2C%20or%20modern%20and%20traditional%2C%20or%20capitalist%2C%20socialist%2C%20and%20underdeveloped%E2%80%9D%20and%20instead%20given%20over%20to%20studying%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20forms%20and%20functions%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Earticulating%20principles%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20social%20organization%20and%20culture%20%E2%80%A6%20viewed%20as%20complex%20sets%20of%20relations%20and%20their%20transformations%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%201974%2C%20emphasis%20in%20original).%20Even%20more%20poignantly%20%E2%80%93%20and%20lending%20substance%20to%20my%20own%20youthful%20urges%20at%20building%20bridges%20across%20divisions%20internal%20to%20the%20social%20sciences%20%E2%80%93%20JPS%20also%20spoke%20about%20the%20essential%20task%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpromot%5Bing%5D%20the%20reconciliation%20of%20our%20two%20institutional%20modes%20of%20learning%2C%20the%20imported%20international%20mode%20and%20the%20inherited%20national%20tradition%2C%20unhappily%20segregated%20for%20so%20long%20to%20the%20point%20of%20intellectual%20self-estrangement%E2%80%9D%20(1974).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20sociology%20of%20European%20science%20and%20modernity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20yet%2C%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20fecundity%20lay%20elsewhere%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Csociology%20of%20European%20science%20and%20modernity%E2%80%9D%20that%20he%20strove%20to%20cultivate%2C%20which%20oversaw%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccritical%20trilogy%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20three%20%E2%80%98little%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Esic%3C%2Fem%3E)%20books%2C%20all%20published%20by%20OUP%2C%20namely%2C%20%3Cem%3EScience%20and%20Culture%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1978)%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Other%20Mind%20of%20Europe%3A%20Goethe%20as%20a%20Scientist%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1984)%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20European%20Modernity%3A%20Science%2C%20Truth%20and%20Method%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2002).%20Interestingly%2C%20all%20the%20three%20works%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20two%2C%20even%20more%20evidently%20so%20%E2%80%93%20bore%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20German%20writer%20Johann%20Wolfgang%20von%20Goethe%20(1749-1832)%2C%20discerning%20in%20the%20latter%20%E2%80%9Can%20alternative%20science%20of%20nature%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cofficial%20positivist-dualist%20methodology%20of%20Copernicus%2C%20Galileo%20and%20Newton.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20of%20course%2C%20my%20own%20engagements%20with%20this%20German%20figure%20have%20evolved%3B%20and%2C%20even%20as%20I%20felt%20the%20rather%20sweeping%20flow%20of%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20rendition%20of%20Goethe%2C%20I%20have%20always%20had%20to%20heed%20the%20philosophical%20merits%20of%20that%20treatment%2C%20specifically%20the%20attempt%20to%20extract%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnon-standard%E2%80%9D%20conception%20of%20scientific%20method%20from%20the%20baffling%20prose%20and%20aphoristic%20style%20of%20Goethe.%C2%A0%20Formulaically%20rendered%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Goethe%20spectrum%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20and%20juxtaposed%20against%20what%20was%20termed%20the%20%E2%80%98Newton%20spectrum%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20JPS%20pointedly%20asked%20(and%20I%20am%20condensing%2C%20albeit%20staying%20with%20his%20flowing%20words)%20%E2%80%9Cas%20to%20whether%20the%20two%20different%20spectra%20of%20Goethe%20and%20Newton%20are%20both%20only%20%E2%80%98models%20of%20reality%E2%80%99%2C%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20or%20perhaps%20also%20to%20be%20classed%20as%20models%20of%20our%20knowledge%20of%20reality%2C%20%E2%80%98models%20of%20truth%E2%80%99%3F%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%2C%20furthermore%2C%20going%20on%20to%20state%3A%20%E2%80%9COr%20can%20there%20be%20still%20a%20third%20possible%20solution%20of%20mediation%20positing%20a%20non-dualist%20relation%20between%20the%20truth%20and%20the%20reality%20as%20the%20object%20of%20science%3F%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%202002).%20Considering%20that%20this%20was%20working%20off%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20discourse%20of%20nature%20uttered%20through%20man%20or%20what%20we%20call%20science%2C%E2%80%9D%20I%20must%20reiterate%20that%20I%20remain%20devoted%20to%20the%20terms%20of%20this%20quest%3B%20my%20questions%2C%20though%2C%20and%20the%20unfolding%20structures%20of%20my%20answering%20have%20since%20got%20complicated%20with%20the%20burgeoning%20scholarship%20in%20the%20history%20and%20philosophy%20of%20science%20(perhaps%20even%20about%20how%20to%20think%20about%20%E2%80%98intelligibility%20in%20science%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20abstract).%20The%20latter%2C%20specifically%2C%20was%20a%20conversation%20I%20was%20hoping%20to%20have%20with%20JPS%2C%20but%20his%20stroke%20in%202015%20put%20paid%20to%20those%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20however%2C%20I%20continued%20to%20engage%20with%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20and%20even%20recall%20random%20conversations%20with%20him%20on%20the%20question%20of%20modernity%20when%20he%20visited%20our%20department%2Funiversity%20as%20a%20fellow%20in%202011%20(or%202012%3F).%20Even%20as%20I%20responded%20to%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20gesture%20of%20thinking%20European%20modernity%20through%20%E2%80%98science%2C%E2%80%99%20I%20was%20not%20entirely%20convinced%20of%20his%20schemata%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20vernacular%20Indian%20modernity%2C%E2%80%9D%20reading%20into%20it%20the%20traces%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98nationalist%E2%80%99%20form%20of%20self-rendition%2C%20albeit%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98swarajist%E2%80%99%20kind.%20I%20could%20not%20follow-up%20on%20this%20matrix%20of%20engagement%2C%20even%20as%20I%20made%20frequent%20annual%20visits%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20at%20DSE%20(between%202008-2018).%20Now%2C%20even%20as%20I%20strive%20to%20make%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20his%20%E2%80%98sociology%20of%20European%20science%20and%20modernity%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20framing%20that%20configures%20it%20looms%20large.%20As%20he%20urged%20in%20a%20precipitate%20form%20in%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EThe%20European%20Modernity%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(2002)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%5BW%5De%20shall%20have%20to%20make%20up%20our%20own%20minds%20independently%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20as%20to%20what%20had%20happened%20and%20how%20in%20the%20European%20modernity%2C%20which%20constitutes%20the%20chief%20single%20source%20of%20all%20our%20imports%20in%20the%20world%20of%20knowledge%2C%20power%20and%20culture.%C2%A0%20One%20can%20then%20begin%20to%20decide%20whether%20there%20exist%20perhaps%20other%20non-standard%20or%20alternative%20traditions%20and%20underground%20tendencies%20which%20could%20redefine%20the%20official%20European%20science%20or%20history%2C%20politics%20and%20economics%20or%20ethics%20handed%20down%20to%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20this%20was%20the%20thought%20that%20anchored%20the%20%E2%80%98European%20Studies%E2%80%99%20programme%20that%20JPS%20initiated%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20at%20DSE%2C%20a%20programme%20instituted%20not%20quite%20as%20an%20area%20studies%20discipline%20(or%20specialisation)%2C%20but%20meant%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Ca%20laboratory%20for%20new%20Indian%20perspectives%20on%20Western%20theories%20and%20practices%20with%20sociology%20and%20social%20anthropology%20viewed%20and%20understood%20as%20a%20single%20spectrum%E2%80%9D%20(Khalid%20Tyabji%2C%202019).%20The%20programme%20never%20took%20off%20though%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20energies%20generated%20by%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98critical%20trilogy%2C%E2%80%99%20as%20enumerated%20at%20the%20start%20of%20this%20section.%20Perhaps%2C%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98experimentalism%E2%80%99%20had%20to%20confront%20its%20limits%2C%20not%20quite%20only%20in%20institutional%20terms%20but%20also%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20disciplinary%20deficit%20that%20defined%20the%20sociology%20and%20social%20anthropology%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20as%20I%20think%20through%20this%2C%20in%20this%20my%20charged%20moment%2C%20the%20formal%20question%20that%20has%20haunted%20the%20key%20spheres%20of%20my%20work%20returns%3A%20about%20what%20%E2%80%98disciplinarity%E2%80%99%20necessarily%20consists%20in%20and%20about%20whether%20a%20purely%20disciplinary%20capacity%20(that%20is%20to%20say%2C%20a%20grounding%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20discipline)%20could%20envisage%20alternative%20perspectives%20which%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20a%20disciplinary%20capacity%20cannot%20occupy.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20to%20me%2C%20I%20now%20realise%2C%20JPS%20epitomised%20this%20possibility%2C%20the%20very%20coherence%20of%20this%20possibility%20(even%20as%20I%20continue%20to%20strive%20to%20address%20what%20this%20might%20yield%20about%20both%20the%20genealogy%20of%20our%20disciplines%20and%20their%20historical%20epistemology).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20too%20another%20possibility%20that%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20sociology%20of%20European%20science%20and%20modernity%2C%20as%20recalled%20in%20its%20precipitate%20form%20above%2C%20holds%20for%20us.%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20equally%20indefatigable%20contemporary%2C%20the%20redoubtable%20Ashis%20Nandy%20(another%20reference%20point%20for%20my%20own%20work)%20had%20toyed%20with%20two%20constructs%20to%20address%20the%20possibilities%20of%20socio-cultural%20and%20political%20criticism%20in%20India%2C%20what%20he%20(Nandy)%20termed%20%E2%80%98critical%20traditionalism%2Ftraditionality%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98critical%20modernism%E2%80%99%20(Nandy%2C%20%E2%80%98Cultural%20Frames%20for%20Social%20Transformation%3A%20A%20Credo%2C%E2%80%99%201987).%20The%20former%20(that%20is%2C%20critical%20traditionalism%2Ftraditionality)%2C%20emblematic%20of%20his%20own%20stance%2C%20marks%20a%20criticism%20of%20modernity%20from%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eoutside%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20modernity%2C%20albeit%20also%20willing%20to%20oppose%20some%20traditions%20vehemently%20(even%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20including%20within%20its%20frame%20elements%20of%20modernity%20as%20critical%20vectors)%3B%20alternatively%2C%20%E2%80%98critical%20modernism%E2%80%99%20is%20taken%20to%20represent%20a%20criticism%20of%20modernity%20from%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Einside%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20modernity%2C%20but%20which%20is%20often%20characterised%20by%20an%20unabashed%20defence%20of%20tradition.%20%5BNote%2C%20Nandy%E2%80%99s%20essay%20fragmentarily%20illustrates%20these%20two%20positions%20through%20the%20contrasting%20orientations%20of%20Gandhi%20and%20Ananda%20K.%20Coomaraswamy%20respectively%2C%20but%20that%20can%20pass!%5D%20The%20choice%20of%20his%20own%20preferred%20position%20is%20clear%20but%2C%20as%20Nandy%20demonstrates%20through%20the%20range%20of%20his%20writings%2C%20the%20decision%20can%20(or%20ought%20to)%20remain%20a%20fraught%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20to%20me%20that%20JPS%20is%20confounding%20the%20very%20terms%20of%20this%20troubled%20choice%2C%20so%20that%20even%20as%20he%20seems%20to%20be%20inheriting%20a%20%E2%80%98critical%20modernism%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20very%20%E2%80%98inside%E2%80%99%20of%20modernity%20is%20being%20torn%20asunder%2C%20dialecticised%20as%20it%20were%20into%20its%20potential%20%E2%80%98outside%E2%80%99%20as%20well.%20I%20realise%20of%20course%20%E2%80%93%20as%20JPS%20too%20does%20%E2%80%93%20that%20any%20vocabulary%20of%20%E2%80%98inside%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98outside%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20complicated%20one%2C%20as%20indeed%20the%20question%20of%20the%20frame%20from%20within%20which%20their%20distinction%20is%20being%20drawn.%20Indeed%2C%20my%20pointed%20allusions%20in%20the%20foregoing%20section%20to%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20work%20on%20the%20history%20and%20semiology%20of%20Sikhism%20were%20meant%20to%20precisely%20underscore%20this%20problem.%20But%20where%20we%20depart%2C%20arguably%2C%20is%20in%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98necessary%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98sufficient%E2%80%99%20conditions%20of%20(or%20for)%20a%20critique%20of%20(Indian)%20modernity.%20The%20tension%20between%20%E2%80%98history%20and%20value%E2%80%99%20endemic%20to%20all%20modernity%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20of%20a%20European%20vintage%20or%20our%20own%20vernacular%20variants%20%E2%80%93%20might%20yet%20require%20to%20be%20thematised%20and%20re-contextualised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBe%20that%20as%20it%20may%2C%20I%20remain%20in%20JPS%E2%80%99s%20debt%20%E2%80%93%20the%20teacher%20one%20never%20had%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20is%20only%20right%20and%20proper%20that%20the%20last%20word%20be%20with%20him%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20advancement%20of%20knowledge%2C%20I%20think%2C%20depends%20upon%20the%20interplay%20of%20method%2C%20theory%20and%20data%20in%20a%20single%20mental%20arena%2C%20local%20or%20universal%2C%20and%20is%20always%20implicitly%20social.%20%C2%A0India%20must%20now%20bid%20for%20its%20competitive%20place%20in%20the%20assumed%20universal%20free%20world%20of%20the%20intellect%2C%20which%20we%20must%20ourselves%20map%20and%20survey%20(swaraj)%2C%20and%20not%20be%20satisfied%20with%20the%20mere%20allotted%20expression%20of%20some%20fixed%20nativist%20quota%20of%20Indianness%20(swadeshi)%3A%20that%20is%2C%20so%20to%20say%2C%20my%20real%20and%20true%20%3Cem%3Eswadharm%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20individual%20conscience%2C%20in%20life%20and%20thought%E2%80%9D%20(JPS%2C%202019%2C%20as%20in%20original).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEverything%20swarajist%20is%20good%20for%20swadeshi%2C%20but%20everything%20swadeshi%20is%20not%20good%20for%20swaraj%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Adieu%20Professor%20Jit%20Pal%20Singh%20Uberoi%20(JPS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESasheej%20Hegde%20teaches%20sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%2C%20and%20is%20in%20the%20final%20leg%20of%20his%20long%20and%