C%20but%20you'll%20know%20exactly%20what%20your%20money%20is%20going%20toward.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20waffle%3A%20Onsen%20Bath%20Towel%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Onsen%20waffle%20towel%20in%20mustard%20yellow%20folded%20on%20a%20gray%20couch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fb81e3c32f2170011f70643%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Onsen%20Bath%20Towel%20is%20a%20lightweight%20and%20resilient%20waffle-weave%20option%20that%20is%20also%20highly%20absorbent.%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E400%C2%A0GSM%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20100%25%20Supima%20cotton%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESizes%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E31%26quot%3B%20x%2057%26quot%3B%3B%2038%26quot%3B%20x%2067%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELight%2C%20dries%20quickly%2C%20comfortable%20texture%2C%20durable%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThinner%20and%20less%20soft%20than%20traditional%20towels%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFluffy%2C%20thick%20terry%20towels%20can%20sometimes%20feel%20stifling%2C%20especially%20if%20your%20body%20temperature%20runs%20hot%20or%20you%20live%20in%20a%20warm%20climate.%20Onsen's%20bath%20towel%20is%20a%20great%20alternative%20because%20it's%20thin%2C%20light%2C%20and%20quick-drying%20but%20still%20highly%20absorbent%20and%20comfortable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20made%20from%20100%25%20Supima%20cotton%2C%20which%20is%20a%20fiber%20that's%20strong%20yet%20soft.%20Adding%20to%20the%20towel's%20durability%20is%20a%20relaxed%20waffle-weave%20construction%20that%20seems%20to%20stretch%20and%20adapt%20to%20however%20you%20handle%20the%20towel.%20Though%20I%20could%20see%20the%20thin%2C%20individual%20fibers%2C%20I%20was%20impressed%20with%20how%20the%20towel%20never%20came%20out%20of%20the%20wash%20with%20frayed%20or%20loose%20threads.%20It%20also%20never%20snagged%20on%20my%20jewelry%2C%20which%20was%20a%20joyous%20revelation%20since%20I%20keep%20my%20earrings%20and%20nose%20ring%20on%20in%20the%20shower%2C%20and%20they%20can%20catch%20even%20on%20terry%20towels.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20bonded%202-inch%20edges%20provide%20structure%20to%20the%20flexible%20fabric.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20has%20the%20measurements%20of%20an%20average-sized%20bath%20towel%2C%20it%20dries%20quickly%20and%20takes%20up%20much%20less%20space%2C%20making%20it%20a%20good%20travel%20towel.%20And%20unlike%20other%20waffle%20weave%20products%20we've%20tried%2C%20the%20Onsen%20towel%20doesn't%20shrink%20in%20the%20wash.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lattice%20texture%20can%20take%20some%20getting%20used%20to%2C%20but%20overall%20the%20material%20feels%20pleasant%20and%20springy.%20The%20towel%20also%20absorbed%20water%20from%20my%20skin%20without%20clinging%20to%20it%2C%20a%20combination%20especially%20welcome%20in%20humid%20weather.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20bath%20towel%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20interior%20shot%20of%20a%20bathroom%20with%20two%20bath%20towels%20hanging%20on%20the%20door.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F645d20c3d391de0019bd93a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20biggest%20factors%20to%20consider%20when%20buying%20the%20best%20towels%20are%20absorbency%2C%20drying%20time%2C%20and%20durability.%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20factors%20you%20should%20take%20into%20consideration%20while%20shopping%20for%20a%20new%20bath%20towel%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EMaterials%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20favorite%20bath%20towels%20are%20all%20made%20from%20cotton%2C%20but%20there%20are%20many%20differences%20between%20the%20types%20of%20cotton%20used%20that%20impact%20the%20texture%20of%20your%20towel.%20Here%20are%20some%20common%20terms%20to%20look%20out%20for%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong-staple%20cotton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECompared%20to%20short-staple%20cotton%2C%20long-staple%20cotton%20has%20longer%2C%20silkier%20fibers%2C%20which%20ultimately%20result%20in%20smoother%20and%20stronger%20yarn.%20Bath%20towels%20made%20from%20long-staple%20cotton%20will%20feel%20soft%20yet%20durable%2C%20and%20they're%20more%20resistant%20to%20fraying%20or%20pilling.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftextiles.ncsu.edu%2Fdirectory%2Fpeople%2Fkleonas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKaren%20Leonas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20textile%20sciences%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftextiles.ncsu.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWilson%20College%20of%20Textiles%2C%20NC%20State%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20industry%20definition%20of%20long-staple%20cotton%20is%20a%20fiber%20length%20of%201.15-1.22%20inches.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExtra-long%20staple%20cotton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20the%20name%20suggests%2C%20extra%20long-staple%20cotton%20has%20even%20longer%20fibers%20than%20long-staple%20cotton.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20it's%20smoother%2C%20more%20flexible%2C%20and%20more%20resistant%20to%20pilling%20than%20long-staple%20cotton.%20Extra-long%20staple%20cotton%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20towel%20materials%20you%20can%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETurkish%20and%20Egyptian%20cotton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BTurkish%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BEgyptian%26quot%3B%20cotton%20refer%20simply%20to%20where%20the%20cotton%20is%20sourced%20from%2C%20not%20necessarily%20its%20quality%20and%20strength.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPima%20and%20Supima%20cotton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPima%20and%20Supima%20cotton%20are%20the%20same%20thing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Supima%20is%20merely%20the%20trademark%20name%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20refers%20to%20extra-long-staple%20cotton%20that%20is%20grown%20only%20in%20the%20US%20and%20has%20a%20fiber%20length%20of%20at%20least%201.5%20inches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECombed%20and%20ring-spun%20cotton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWith%20combed%20cotton%2C%20the%20cotton%20fibers%20are%20treated%20before%20they%20are%20spun%20into%20yarn.%20They%20are%20brushed%20to%20remove%20shorter%20fibers%20and%20any%20impurities.%20With%20ring-spun%20cotton%2C%20the%20fibers%20are%20spun%20and%20twisted%20together%20to%20create%20longer%2C%20stronger%20threads.%20The%20two%20terms%20can%20be%20independent%20of%20each%20other%3A%20combed%20cotton%20isn't%20necessarily%20ring-spun%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%20It's%20also%20possible%20for%20both%20techniques%20to%20be%20present%20in%20your%20cotton%20towel.%20Either%20way%2C%20combed%20and%20ring-spun%20are%20ways%20to%20make%20the%20cotton%2C%20and%20thus%20your%20bath%20towel%2C%20softer%20and%20stronger.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsorbency%20and%20drying%20speed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20bath%20towel%20will%20efficiently%20dry%20off%20your%20whole%20body%20in%20just%20a%20few%20pats%2C%20but%20high%20absorbency%20may%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20drying%20speed%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20absorbent%20towels%20tend%20to%20be%20heavier%20and%20take%20longer%20to%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20assess%20absorbency%2C%20look%20at%20material%20(cotton%20is%20best)%20and%20GSM%20(grams%20per%20square%20meter).%20GSM%20stands%20for%20grams%20per%20square%20meter%20and%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20towel%20density.%20The%20higher%20the%20GSM%2C%20the%20heavier%20and%20more%20absorbent%20the%20towel%20is%2C%20and%20the%20longer%20it%20will%20take%20to%20dry.%20%26quot%3BTypically%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20GSM%20(900%20is%20considered%20very%20high)%2C%20the%20more%20luxe%20and%20plush%20the%20towel.%20A%20lower%20GSM%20(300%20would%20be%20pretty%20low)%20indicates%20a%20lighter%20weight%20and%20more%20quick-drying%20towel%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Emily%20Forrest%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20towels%20at%20the%20wedding%20registry%20site%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_042718_best-towels-20%26h%3D7a5791e4e2fdbf5d6941cd5754a4e0064813bc8b564cd4790bd238fe62f33ede%26postID%3D61b8efc6f2a36b1ac9f41acf%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-towels%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.zola.com%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZola%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20says%20the%20best%20towels%20usually%20have%20a%20GSM%20between%20400-600%3B%20not%20too%20thick%20and%20not%20too%20thin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ESize%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBath%20towels%20usually%20measure%2028%20to%2031%20inches%20wide%20and%2054%20to%2058%20inches%20long.%20They're%20designed%20to%20wrap%20comfortably%20around%20the%20shoulders%20and%20torso%20of%20an%20average%20person%2C%20but%20depending%20on%20your%20height%2C%20size%2C%20and%20personal%20preferences%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20pay%20closer%20attention%20to%20the%20towel's%20dimensions.%20If%20bath%20towels%20feel%20small%2C%20try%20shopping%20for%20bath%20sheets%20instead%2C%20which%20are%20usually%2035%20to%2040%20inches%20wide%20and%2068%20to%2072%20inches%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDurability%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20you'll%20use%20your%20towel%20every%20day%2C%20fabric%20strength%20is%20of%20utmost%20importance.%20You'll%20want%20something%20that%20can%20stand%20up%20to%20hundreds%20of%20uses%20in%20a%20year%20and%20doesn't%20fray%20or%20get%20scratchy.%20Long-staple%20and%20extra%20long-staple%20cotton%2C%20with%20their%20long%20fibers%2C%20are%20strong%20and%20resistant%20to%20fraying%20and%20pilling.%20The%20type%20of%20weave%20also%20affects%20strength.%20Our%20favorite%20waffle%20towel%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20a%20stretchy%20and%20adaptable%20construction%20that's%20also%20extra%20durable%20and%20never%20seems%20to%20come%20loose.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECertifications%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOeko%20Tex%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20may%20notice%20that%20some%20of%20our%20best%20towel%20picks%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oeko-tex.com%2Fen%2Four-standards%2Fstandard-100-by-oeko-tex%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOeko%20Tex%20certification%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20label%20means%20the%20final%20product%20has%20been%20independently%20tested%20for%20more%20than%20100%20harmful%20chemical%20substances%20and%20is%20safe%20for%20human%20use.%20While%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20certification%20out%20there%2C%20it's%20widely%20used%20and%20known%20in%20the%20textile%20industry.%20Our%20experts%20say%20you%20should%20look%20for%20the%20Oeko-Tex%20Standard%20100%20certification%20for%20basic%20safety%2C%20but%20if%20you%20also%20care%20about%20manufacturing%2C%20look%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oeko-tex.com%2Fen%2Four-standards%2Fstep-by-oeko-tex%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESTeP%20by%20Oeko%20Tex%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20checks%20for%20environmentally%20friendly%2C%20socially%20responsible%2C%20and%20safe%20practices%20all%20along%20the%20production%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGOTS%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal-standard.org%2Fthe-standard%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Organic%20Textile%20Standard%20(GOTS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20another%20certification%20used%20specifically%20for%20organic%20textiles.%20GOTS-certified%20sheets%20contain%20at%20least%2095%25%20certified%20organic%20fibers%20and%20meet%20environmental%20and%20social%20standards%20at%20every%20stage%20of%20processing%20and%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20test%20bath%20towels%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person's%20hand%20folding%20a%20fluffy%20white%20towel%20with%20black%20edging.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fb8256532f2170011f7068f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20part%20of%20our%20testing%20methodology%20for%20the%20best%20towel%2C%20we%20used%20each%20in%20real-life%20conditions.%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20search%20for%20the%20best%20towel%2C%20we%20tested%2014%20products%20and%20put%20them%20through%20the%20same%20tests%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsorbency%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20used%20each%20towel%20to%20dry%20my%20entire%20body%20after%20a%20shower%20and%20wring%20out%20water%20from%20my%20wet%20hair%20(I%20have%20thick%2C%20medium-coarse%20hair).%20I%20repeated%20this%20test%20multiple%20times%20over%20the%20course%20of%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrying%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20timed%20how%20long%20each%20towel%20took%20to%20dry%20completely%20when%20hung%20normally%20on%20a%20towel%20bar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EComfort%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20best%20towel%20should%20be%20cozy%20and%20comfortable%20to%20use.%20I%20noted%20softness%2C%20fluffiness%2C%20and%20thickness%20and%20how%20the%20towel%20clung%20to%20or%20wicked%20water%20off%20damp%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDurability%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20washed%20each%20towel%20and%20evaluated%20it%20for%20shrinkage%2C%20fraying%2C%20color%20loss%2C%20and%20roughness%20over%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBath%20towel%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20closeup%20shot%20of%20a%20cotton%20towel%20label%20stating%20the%20construction%20and%20country%20of%20origin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F645d21e0d391de0019bd93ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20tag%20shows%20many%20of%20the%20terms%20you%20may%20see%20when%20shopping%20for%20towels.%3Cp%3EConnie%20Chen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch4%3EWhat%20is%20the%20difference%20between%20bath%20sheets%20and%20bath%20towels%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20towels%20we%20test%20and%20review%20here%20are%20bath%20towels%20and%20typically%20measure%20around%2028%20to%2031%20inches%20wide%20and%2054%20to%2058%20inches%20long.%20Bath%20towels%20are%20designed%20to%20drape%20around%20your%20shoulders%20or%20comfortably%20wrap%20around%20your%20body%2C%20but%20if%20you%20want%20even%20more%20coverage%2C%20you'll%20want%20the%20much%20larger%20bath%20sheet.%20Bath%20sheets%20typically%20measure%2035%20to%2040%20inches%20wide%20and%2068%20to%2072%20inches%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20increase%20in%20size%20also%20means%20bath%20sheets%20are%20more%20expensive%20and%20take%20longer%20to%20dry%20than%20bath%20towels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch4%3EHow%20often%20should%20I%20wash%20my%20bath%20towels%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EWash%20your%20towels%20before%20you%20use%20them%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20then%20after%20every%20three%20to%20four%20uses.%20A%20bath%20towel%20may%20seem%20relatively%20clean%20since%20you%20only%20use%20it%20to%20dry%20off%20after%20a%20shower%2C%20but%20that's%20actually%20not%20the%20case%3A%20towels%20provide%20a%20rich%20environment%20for%20bacteria%20to%20build%20up%20and%20grow.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20about%20when%20you%20dry%20yourself%20off%20with%20your%20towel%20%E2%80%94%20you%20are%20collecting%20oils%20and%20skin%2C%20and%20so%20you%20want%20to%20wash%20your%20towels%20every%20few%20uses.%20%5BThat's%20also%5D%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20a%20stocked%20linen%20closet%2C%26quot%3B%20Forrest%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch4%3EWhat%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20wash%20towels%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20regular%20clean%2C%20use%20warm%20or%20hot%20water%20and%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20detergent%20in%20the%20washing%20machine.%20Be%20warned%20that%20too%20much%20detergent%20can%20lead%20to%20residue%20buildup%2C%20which%20affects%20the%20towel's%20absorbency%20and%20fluff.%20In%20addition%2C%20manufacturers%20often%20add%20finishes%20or%20softeners%20to%20the%20towel%2C%20further%20contributing%20to%20buildup.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20deeper%20clean%2C%20wash%20it%20in%20a%20hot%20cycle%20with%20a%20cup%20of%20white%20vinegar%2C%20and%20then%20run%20it%20in%20a%20second%20wash%20cycle%20with%20half%20a%20cup%20of%20baking%20soda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20washing%2C%20you%20can%20toss%20it%20in%20the%20dryer%20on%20low%20or%20medium%20heat.%20Add%20a%20wool%20dryer%20ball%20to%20help%20with%20drying%20efficiency%20and%20soften%20the%20fabric.%20Be%20sure%20to%20clean%20the%20lint%20trap%20after%20each%20use%2C%20as%20towels%20are%20prone%20to%20shedding.%20Line%20drying%20is%20an%20option%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch4%3EHow%20long%20do%20towels%20last%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20depends%20on%20how%20often%20you%20rotate%20your%20towels%20out%20as%20well%20as%20the%20material%20they're%20made%20out%20of.%20Generally%2C%20bath%20towels%20should%20last%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20with%20good%20maintenance.%20If%20there's%20excessive%20fraying%2C%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20as%20soft%20or%20fluffy%20as%20it%20used%20to%2C%20or%20if%20there's%20a%20lingering%20smell%20you%20just%20can't%20seem%20to%20get%20rid%20of%2C%20then%20it's%20probably%20time%20to%20buy%20a%20new%20towel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch4%3EHow%20should%20I%20store%20bath%20towels%20when%20not%20in%20use%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EHang%20your%20towel%20on%20a%20hook%20or%20towel%20bar%20when%20not%20in%20use%2C%20making%20sure%20the%20towel%20has%20plenty%20of%20space%20for%20air%20to%20circulate.%20This%20speeds%20up%20drying%20time%20and%20prevents%20mildew%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20clean%2C%20dry%20towels%20meant%20for%20longer-term%20storage%2C%20you%20can%20fold%20or%20roll%20them%2C%20then%20stack%20them%20in%20your%20linen%20closet%20or%20cabinet.%20However%20you%20choose%20to%20arrange%20them%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20storage%20space%20is%20cool%20and%20dry%20and%20that%20your%20towels%20are%20completely%20dry%20before%20you%20store%20them%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch4%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20do%20my%20towels%20smell%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20wet%20towel%20is%20left%20bunched%20up%20in%20the%20hamper%20or%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20mildew%20starts%20to%20grow%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20musty%20smell.%20To%20avoid%20mildew%2C%20hang%20your%20towel%20right%20after%20use%20so%20it%20has%20the%20space%20and%20time%20to%20dry%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20still%20smells%2C%20use%20our%20deep%20clean%20method%3A%20wash%20it%20in%20a%20hot%20cycle%20with%20a%20cup%20of%20white%20vinegar%2C%20and%20then%20run%20it%20in%20a%20second%20wash%20cycle%20with%20half%20a%20cup%20of%20baking%20soda.%20Dry%20it%20in%20a%20machine%20or%20hang%20it%20up%20to%20line-dry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch4%3EWhy%20do%20my%20towels%20stain%20or%20become%20discolored%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20possible%20culprits%20for%20stains%20and%20discoloration%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESkincare%20products%20that%20contain%20benzoyl%20peroxide.%20People%20who%20regularly%20use%20benzoyl%20peroxide%20products%20may%20want%20to%20consider%20sticking%20to%20white%20or%20light-colored%20towels.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUsing%20fabric%20softener%20or%20bleach%20in%20the%20washing%20machine.%20Even%20if%20you%20don't%20actively%20add%20bleach%2C%20leftover%20bleach%20in%20the%20dispenser%20can%20sometimes%20leak%20into%20the%20current%20load.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-towels%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706912273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543f90236d588dc55c9