0in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Friday%2C%20February%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20meeting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeign.gov.mv%2Findex.php%2Fen%2Fmedia-center%2Fstatements%2Fstatement-by-foreign-minister-moosa-zameer-at-the-eu-indo-pacific-ministerial-forum-2024-stmt-5%5C%22%3Ethe%20Maldivian%20foreign%20ministry%20issued%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20sides%20agreed%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20will%20replace%20the%20military%20personnel%20in%20one%20of%20the%20three%20aviation%20platform%20by%2010%20March%202024%2C%20and%20will%20complete%20replacing%20military%20personnel%20in%20the%20other%20two%20platforms%20by%2010%20May%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37511%2FFirst_meeting_of_the_IndiaMaldives_High_Level_Core_Group%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20external%20affair%E2%80%99s%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20give%20the%20details.%20It%20only%20stated%20that%20both%20countries%20had%20%E2%80%9Cagreed%20on%20a%20set%20of%20mutually%20workable%20solutions%20to%20enable%20continued%20operation%20of%20Indian%20aviation%20platforms%20that%20provide%20humanitarian%20and%20medvac%20services%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Maldives%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20from%20the%20Maldivian%20foreign%20ministry%20does%20not%20provide%20clarity%20on%20whether%20the%20Indian%20military%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20civilians%2C%20who%20could%20even%20be%20ex-servicemen.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20certainly%20clear%20that%20the%20Dornier%20and%20two%20helicopters%20gifted%20by%20India%20would%20remain%20in%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20rather%20positive%20outcome%20for%20Maldivian%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20who%20had%20asked%20India%20to%20withdraw%20all%20its%20military%20personnel%20operating%20the%20three%20aircraft%20in%20by%20March%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuizzu%E2%80%99s%20successful%20campaign%20in%20the%20Presidential%20polls%20was%20largely%20based%20on%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign.%20Began%20in%202020%20by%20former%20president%20Abdulla%20Yameen%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign%20aimed%20to%20corner%20the%20ruling%20Solih%20administration%20for%20his%20close%20links%20to%20New%20Delhi%20by%20claiming%20that%20presence%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20Maldivian%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20after%20taking%20the%20oath%20of%20office%2C%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20of%20Maldives%20officially%20requested%20India%20to%20withdraw%20its%20troops%20from%20the%20country.%20When%20he%20met%20with%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Dubai%2C%20both%20argeed%20to%20set%20up%20a%20committee%20of%20officials%20to%20discuss%20the%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Muizzu%20gave%20the%20ultimatum%20of%20March%2015%20at%20the%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20committee%20last%20month%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20Maldives%20did%20not%20want%20India%20to%20drag%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Maldives%20set%20to%20go%20for%20parliamentary%20elections%20next%20month%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20an%20imminent%20removal%20of%20Indian%20military%20troops%20will%20certainly%20boost%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20election%20hopes.%20Currently%2C%20Muizzu%20is%20facing%20difficulties%20in%20getting%20his%20ministers%20endorsed%20from%20the%20MDP-dominated%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706897473000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14103358%2FGDvFFVLbgAAmZK2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-to-replace-military-personnel-operating-aircraft-helicopters-maldives%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20second%20meeting%20of%20the%20core%20group%20from%20two%20countries%20that%20was%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20was%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Friday%2C%20February%202.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-to-replace-military-personnel-operating-aircraft-helicopters-maldives%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Italian%20mafia%20boss%20who%20escaped%20from%20prison%20using%20bed%20sheets%20recaptured%20in%20France%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706897332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F57C9%2Fproduction%2F_132537422_de27.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68186499%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Marco%20Raduano%20had%20been%20on%20the%20run%20for%20a%20year%20before%20he%20was%20tracked%20down%20in%20Corsica%2C%20France.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68186499%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68186499.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68186499.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Man%20in%20French%20court%20over%20missing%20endangered%20monkeys%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706897323000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F112EF%2Fproduction%2F_132538307_saimarigetty.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68187246%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2020-year-old%20suspect%20denies%20stealing%2014%20rare%20squirrel%20monkeys%20from%20a%20tropical%20zoo%20near%20Marseille.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68187246%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68187246.