F2024%2F01%2F30%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Faid-gaza-israel.html%5C%22%3Edownplay%20the%20significance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20pause%20in%20funding%2C%20the%20action%20is%20not%20in%20keeping%20with%20precedent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20donors%20did%20not%2C%20for%20example%2C%20defund%20other%20U.N.%20agencies%20or%20peacekeeping%20operations%20amid%20accusations%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2020%2F01%2F11%2Fun-peacekeeping-has-sexual-abuse-problem%5C%22%3Esexual%20assault%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-sdny%2Fpr%2Fformer-un-general-assembly-president-and-five-others-charged-13-million-bribery-scheme%5C%22%3Ecorruption%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Flegacy%2Fsummaries%2Fs.bosnia9510.html%5C%22%3Ecomplicity%20in%20war%20crimes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20real%20terms%2C%20the%20funding%20cuts%20to%20the%20UNRWA%20will%20affect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhere-we-work%2Fgaza-strip%5C%22%3E1.7%20million%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20with%20an%20additional%20400%2C000%20Palestinians%20without%20refugee%20status%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20benefit%20from%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure.%20Some%20critics%20have%20gone%20further%20and%20said%20depriving%20the%20agency%20of%20funds%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjacobin.com%2F2024%2F01%2Funrwa-defunding-gaza-israel%5C%22%3Eamounts%20to%20collective%20punishment%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERefugee%20aid%2C%20and%20humanitarian%20aid%20more%20generally%2C%20is%20theoretically%20meant%20to%20be%20neutral%20and%20impartial.%20But%20as%20experts%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Freluctant-reception%2F558E2A93FF99B8F295347A8FA2053698%5C%22%3Emigration%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FUN-Global-Compacts-Governing-Migrants-and-Refugees%2FMicinski%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367218836%5C%22%3Eand%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.umich.edu%2FBooks%2FD%2FDelegating-Responsibility%5C%22%3Einternational%20relations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20know%20funding%20is%20often%20used%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20tool%2C%20whereby%20allies%20are%20rewarded%20and%20enemies%20punished.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20we%20believe%20the%20cuts%20in%20funding%20for%20the%20UNRWA%20fit%20a%20wider%20pattern%20of%20the%20politicization%20of%20aid%20to%20refugees%2C%20particularly%20Palestinian%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20UNRWA%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNRWA%2C%20short%20for%20the%20U.N.%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%20for%20Palestine%20Refugees%20in%20the%20Near%20East%2C%20was%20established%20two%20years%20after%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-nakba-at-75-palestinians-struggle-to-get-recognition-for-their-catastrophe-204782%5C%22%3E750%2C000%20Palestinians%20were%20expelled%20or%20fled%20from%20their%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20in%201948%20and%20the%20subsequent%20Arab-Israeli%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20creation%2C%20international%20and%20local%20organizations%2C%20many%20of%20them%20religious%2C%20provided%20services%20to%20displaced%20Palestinians.%20But%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Esurveying%20the%20extreme%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20dire%20situation%20pervasive%20across%20refugee%20camps%2C%20the%20U.N.%20General%20Assembly%2C%20including%20all%20Arab%20states%20and%20Israel%2C%20voted%20to%20create%20the%20UNRWA%20in%201949.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20that%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhat-we-do%5C%22%3Ethe%20UNRWA%20has%20been%20the%20primary%20aid%20organization%3C%2Fa%3E%20providing%20food%2C%20medical%20care%2C%20schooling%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20housing%20for%20the%206%20million%20Palestinians%20living%20across%20its%20five%20fields%3A%20Jordan%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20Syria%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20areas%20that%20make%20up%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20territories%3A%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mass%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-nakba-at-75-palestinians-struggle-to-get-recognition-for-their-catastrophe-204782%5C%22%3ENakba%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccatastrophe%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20occurred%20prior%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Fabout-unhcr%2Fwho-we-are%2F1951-refugee-convention%5C%22%3E1951%20Refugee%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20defined%20refugees%20as%20anyone%20with%20a%20well-founded%20fear%20of%20persecution%20owing%20to%20%E2%80%9Cevents%20occurring%20in%20Europe%20before%201%20January%201951.%E2%80%9D%20Despite%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Flegacy-pdf%2F4ec262df9.pdf%5C%22%3E1967%20protocol%20extending%20the%20definition%3C%2Fa%3E%20worldwide%2C%20Palestinians%20are%20still%20excluded%20from%20the%20primary%20international%20system%20protecting%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20UNRWA%20is%20responsible%20for%20providing%20services%20to%20Palestinian%20refugees%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20also%20created%20the%20U.N.%20Conciliation%20Commission%20for%20Palestine%20in%201948%20to%20seek%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.refworld.org%2Fdocid%2F4fe2e5672.html%5C%22%3Elong-term%20political%20solution%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%E2%80%9Cto%20facilitate%20the%20repatriation%2C%20resettlement%20and%20economic%20and%20social%20rehabilitation%20of%20the%20refugees%20and%20the%20payment%20of%20compensation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20UNRWA%20does%20not%20have%20a%20mandate%20to%20push%20for%20the%20traditional%20durable%20solutions%20available%20in%20other%20refugee%20situations.%20As%20it%20happened%2C%20the%20conciliation%20commission%20was%20active%20only%20for%20a%20few%20years%20and%20has%20since%20been%20sidelined%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20U.S.-brokered%20peace%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20the%20UNRWA%20political%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNRWA%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.migrationpolicy.org%2Farticle%2Fpalestinian-refugees-dispossession%5C%22%3Esubject%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20political%20headwinds%20since%20its%20inception%20and%20especially%20during%20periods%20of%20heightened%20tension%20between%20Palestinians%20and%20Israelis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20a%20U.N.%20organization%20and%20thus%20ostensibly%20apolitical%2C%20it%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Efrequently%20been%20criticized%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Palestinians%2C%20Israelis%20as%20well%20as%20donor%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20United%20States%2C%20for%20acting%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNRWA%20performs%20statelike%20functions%20across%20its%20five%20fields%20%E2%80%93%20including%20education%2C%20health%20and%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20is%20restricted%20in%20its%20mandate%20from%20performing%20political%20or%20security%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitial%20Palestinian%20objections%20to%20the%20UNRWA%20stemmed%20from%20the%20organization%E2%80%99s%20early%20focus%20on%20economic%20integration%20of%20refugees%20into%20host%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20UNRWA%20officially%20adhered%20to%20the%20U.N.%20General%20Assembly%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fcontent%2Fresolution-194%5C%22%3EResolution%20194%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20called%20for%20the%20return%20of%20Palestine%20refugees%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20U.N.%2C%20U.K.%20and%20U.S.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Eofficials%20searched%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20means%20by%20which%20to%20resettle%20and%20integrate%20Palestinians%20into%20host%20states%2C%20viewing%20this%20as%20the%20favorable%20political%20solution%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20refugee%20situation%20and%20the%20broader%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict.%20In%20this%20sense%2C%20Palestinians%20perceived%20the%20UNRWA%20to%20be%20both%20highly%20political%20and%20actively%20working%20against%20their%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20later%20decades%2C%20the%20UNRWA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Eswitched%20its%20primary%20focus%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20jobs%20to%20education%20at%20the%20urging%20of%20Palestinian%20refugees.%20But%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20education%20materials%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Eviewed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Israel%20as%20further%20feeding%20Palestinian%20militancy%2C%20and%20the%20Israeli%20government%20insisted%20on%20checking%20and%20approving%20all%20materials%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20which%20it%20has%20occupied%20since%201967.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Israel%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Elong%20been%20suspicious%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20refugee%20camps%20and%20in%20providing%20education%2C%20the%20organization%E2%80%99s%20operation%2C%20which%20is%20internationally%20funded%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crisisgroup.org%2Fmiddle-east-north-africa%2Feast-mediterranean-mena%2Fisraelpalestine%2F242-unrwas-reckoning-preserving-un-agency-serving-palestinian-refugees%5C%22%3Ealso%20saves%3C%2Fa%3E%20Israel%20millions%20of%20dollars%20each%20year%20in%20services%20it%20would%20be%20obliged%20to%20deliver%20as%20the%20occupying%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%201960s%2C%20the%20U.S.%20%E2%80%93%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20primary%20donor%20%E2%80%93%20and%20other%20Western%20countries%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%20expressed%20their%20desire%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20use%20aid%20to%20prevent%20radicalization%20among%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20increased%20presence%20of%20armed%20opposition%20groups%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcup.columbia.edu%2Fbook%2Frefuge-and-resistance%2F9780231202855%5C%22%3EU.S.%20attached%20a%20provision%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20UNRWA%20aid%20in%201970%2C%20requiring%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CUNRWA%20take%20all%20possible%20measures%20to%20assure%20that%20no%20part%20of%20the%20United%20States%20contribution%20shall%20be%20used%20to%20furnish%20assistance%20to%20any%20refugee%20who%20is%20receiving%20military%20training%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20so-called%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20or%20any%20other%20guerrilla-type%20organization.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNRWA%20adheres%20to%20this%20requirement%2C%20even%20publishing%20an%20annual%20list%20of%20its%20employees%20so%20that%20host%20governments%20can%20vet%20them%2C%20but%20it%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crisisgroup.org%2Fmiddle-east-north-africa%2Feast-mediterranean-mena%2Fisraelpalestine%2F242-unrwas-reckoning-preserving-un-agency-serving-palestinian-refugees%5C%22%3Eemploys%2030%2C000%20individuals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20whom%20are%20Palestinian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuestions%20over%20the%20links%20of%20the%20UNRWA%20to%20any%20militancy%20has%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20Israeli%20and%20international%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcufi.org%2Fissue%2Funrwa-teachers-continue-to-support-antisemitism-terrorism-on-social-media-un-watch%2F%5C%22%3Ewatch%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20document%20the%20social%20media%20activity%20of%20the%20organization%E2%80%99s%20large%20Palestinian%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERepeated%20cuts%20in%20funding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20used%20its%20money%20and%20power%20within%20the%20U.N.%20to%20block%20criticism%20of%20Israel%2C%20vetoing%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdepts%2Fdhl%2Fresguide%2Fscact_veto_table_en.htm%5C%22%3E45%20U.N.%20resolutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20critical%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20latest%20freeze%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20U.S.%20has%20cut%20funding%20to%20the%20UNRWA%20or%20other%20U.N.%20agencies%20in%20response%20to%20issues%20pertaining%20to%20the%20status%20of%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2FidUSTRE79U5ED%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DWASHINGTON%2520(Reuters)%2520%252D%2520The%2520United%2Cgrant%2520the%2520Palestinians%2520full%2520membership.%5C%22%3EU.S.%20cut%20all%20funding%20to%20UNESCO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20U.N.%20agency%20that%20provides%20educational%20and%20cultural%20programs%20around%20the%20world%2C%20after%20the%20agency%20voted%20to%20admit%20the%20state%20of%20Palestine%20as%20a%20full%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Obama%20administration%20defended%20the%20move%2C%20claiming%20it%20was%20required%20by%20a%201990s%20law%20to%20defund%20any%20U.N.%20body%20that%20admitted%20Palestine%20as%20a%20full%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20action%20was%20nonetheless%20severe.%20Within%20just%20four%20years%2C%20UNESCO%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2F1758-5899.12459%5C%22%3Eforced%20to%20cut%20its%20staff%20in%20half%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20roll%20back%20its%20operations.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fpolitics%2Fu-s-and-israel-officially-withdraw-from-unesco%5C%22%3Ewithdrew%20the%20U.S.%20completely%20from%20UNESCO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20paused%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F08%2F31%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-unrwa-palestinians.html%5C%22%3EUS%2460%20million%20contribution%20to%20the%20UNRWA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Trump%20claimed%20the%20pause%20would%20create%20political%20pressure%20for%20Palestinians%20to%20negotiate.%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20restarted%20U.S.%20contributions%20to%20the%20UNRWA%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoliticization%20of%20refugee%20aid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinian%20are%20not%20the%20only%20group%20to%20suffer%20from%20the%20politicization%20of%20refugee%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20World%20War%20II%2C%20states%20established%20different%20international%20organizations%20to%20help%20refugees%20but%20strategically%20excluded%20some%20groups%20from%20the%20refugee%20definition.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20U.S.%20funded%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalww2museum.org%2Fwar%2Farticles%2Flast-million-eastern-european-displaced-persons-postwar-germany%5C%22%3EU.N.%20Relief%20and%20Rehabilitation%20Administration%20to%20help%20resettle%20displaced%20persons%20after%20World%20War%20II%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20resisted%20Soviet%20pressure%20to%20forcibly%20repatriate%20Soviet%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20also%20created%20a%20separate%20organization%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fijrl%2Farticle-abstract%2F1%2F4%2F501%2F1598187%5C%22%3Ethe%20precursor%20to%20the%20International%20Organization%20for%20Migration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20circumvent%20Soviet%20influence.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20existence%20and%20the%20exclusion%20of%20Palestinian%20refugees%20from%20the%20wider%20refugee%20regime%20parallels%20this%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFunding%20for%20refugees%20has%20also%20been%20politicized%20through%20the%20earmarking%20of%20voluntary%20contributions%20to%20U.N.%20agencies.%20Some%20agencies%20receive%20funding%20from%20U.N.%20dues%3B%20but%20the%20UNRWA%2C%20alongside%20the%20U.N.%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20Refugees%20and%20the%20International%20Organization%20for%20Migration%2C%20receive%20the%20majority%20of%20their%20funding%20from%20voluntary%20contributions%20from%20member%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20contributions%20can%20be%20earmarked%20for%20specific%20activities%20or%20locations%2C%20leading%20to%20donors%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.peio.me%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2FPEIO12_paper_107.pdf%5C%22%3EU.S.%20or%20European%20Union%20dictating%20which%20refugees%20get%20aid%20and%20which%20do%20not%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Earmarked%20contributions%20amounted%20to%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funsceb.org%2Ffs-revenue-agency%5C%22%3E96%25%20of%20the%20UNHCR%E2%80%99s%20budget%2C%2096%25%20of%20the%20IOM%E2%80%99s%20budget%20and%2074%25%20of%20UNRWA%20funding%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20any%20cuts%20to%20UNRWA%20funding%20will%20affect%20its%20ability%20to%20service%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20at%20a%20time%20when%20so%20many%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F01%2F30%2Fmiddleeast%2Ffamine-looms-in-gaza-israel-war-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Efacing%20hunger%2C%20disease%20and%20displacement%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20result%20of%20war.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F222263%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fnicholas-r-micinski-207353%5C%22%3ENicholas%20R.%20Micinski%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%20and%20International%20Affairs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-maine-2120%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Maine%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fkelsey-norman-862895%5C%22%3EKelsey%20Norman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Fellow%20for%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Rice%20University%E2%80%99s%20Baker%20Institute%20for%20Public%20Policy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Frice-university-931%5C%22%3ERice%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Ffunding-for-refugees-has-long-been-politicized-punitive-action-against-unrwa-and-palestinians-fits-that-pattern-222263%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706883358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28113617%2FGE4er87XgAAfTop.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffunding-for-refugees-has-long-been-politicised-action-against-unrwa-palestinians-fits-that-pattern%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20funding%20cuts%20to%20the%20UNRWA%20will%20affect%201.7%20million%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20Gaza%20along%20with%20an%20additional%20400%2C000%20Palestinians%20without%20refugee%20status%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20benefit%20from%20the%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffunding-for-refugees-has-long-been-politicised-action-against-unrwa-palestinians-fits-that-pattern%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Hadinelentu%E2%80%99%3A%20Prithvi%20Konanur%E2%80%99s%20Film%20on%20Teenagers%20Is%20a%20Finely%20Observed%20Document%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Inequities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02191734%2Fimage-1790.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPrithvi%20Konanur%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHadinelentu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(English%20title%3A%20%3Cem%3ESeventeeners%3C%2Fem%3E)%20is%20hardly%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98funny%E2%80%99%20film%2C%20but%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20to%20enter%20the%20film%20through%20a%20sporadic%20moment%20of%20humour.%20Life%2C%20after%20all%2C%20can%20be%20absurdly%20comical%2C%20especially%20when%20viewed%20from%20a%20distance.%20Hari%20(Neeraj%20Matthew)%20and%20Deepa%20(Sherlyn%20Bhosale)%20are%20sitting%20on%20a%20bench%20outside%20the%20principal%E2%80%99s%20office%20at%20their%20junior%20college.%20A%20teacher%2C%20barking%20at%20students%20to%20go%20inside%20their%20class%2C%20comes%20across%20these%20two.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20two%E2%80%A6%20sit%20apart%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20orders.%20It%E2%80%99s%20funny%20because%20the%20teacher%20is%20clearly%20unaware%20why%20Hari%20and%20Deepa%20are%20seated%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudents%20of%20the%2012th%20grade%2C%20Hari%20and%20Deepa%20had%20let%20their%20raging%20passions%20take%20over%2C%20and%20filmed%20themselves%20having%20sex%20in%20an%20empty%20classroom%20of%20the%20college.%20The%20video%20surfaced%20on%20porn%20websites%20and%20was%20widely%20circulated.%20The%20principal%20is%20speaking%20to%20their%20parents%2C%20mulling%20over%20whether%20to%20expel%20them.%20Maybe%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20bit%20late%20to%20tell%20them%20to%20sit%20apart.%20Maybe%2C%20such%20moral%20policing%20and%20a%20widespread%20culture%20of%20sexual%20repression%20is%20what%20caused%20the%20youngsters%20to%20%E2%80%98transgress%E2%80%99%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECo-written%20by%20Konanur%20and%20Anupama%20Hegde%20(a%20lawyer%20by%20profession)%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EHadinelentu%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20a%20composite%20word%20made%20from%20%3Cem%3EHadinelu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%E2%80%9817%E2%80%99%20in%20Kannada)%20and%20%3Cem%3EHadinentu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%E2%80%9818%E2%80%99%20in%20Kannada)%2C%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20two%20teenagers%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20teenage%20and%20adulthood%2C%20%E2%80%98caught%20in%20a%20compromised%20circumstance%E2%80%99.%20What%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20coming-of-age%20tale%20for%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20two%20protagonists%20through%20a%20hellish%20year%2C%20reveals%20itself%20soon%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20two%20teenagers%20reach%20the%20principal%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20Hari%E2%80%99s%20parents%20%E2%80%93%20a%20middle-class%20couple%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%20devastated%20by%20their%20son%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20face%20it%20with%20pragmatism.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Deepa%E2%80%99s%20mother%20is%20a%20cook%20at%20the%20local%20government%20school%2C%20and%20has%20two%20elder%20sisters%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20are%20married.%20Deepa%20is%20the%20first%20from%20the%20family%20to%20have%20studied%20till%20the%2012th%20grade.%20We%20begin%20to%20sense%20how%20the%20consequences%20for%20the%20same%20actions%20will%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20very%20different%20for%20Hari%20and%20Deepa.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20where%20they%20hail%20from%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKonanur%E2%80%99s%20is%20a%20rare%20film%20that%20borrows%20generously%20from%20life%2C%20where%20the%20craft%20is%20nearly%20invisible%20%E2%80%93%20the%20performances%20feel%20naturalistic.%20Whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20principal%20Badri%20(Ravi%20Hebballi)%20or%20vice%20principal%20Seetha%20(Rekha%20Kudligi)%2C%20Hari%E2%80%99s%20parents%20or%20Deepa%E2%80%99s%20mother%20%E2%80%93%20none%20of%20it%20feels%20like%20%E2%80%9Cacting%E2%80%9D.%20The%20courtroom%20scenes%20are%20shockingly%20straightforward%2C%20the%20dialogue%20embedded%20in%20a%20deluge%20of%20legalese%2C%20putting%20the%20audience%20in%20the%20same%20state%20of%20confusion%20as%20the%20characters%2C%20not%20able%20to%20decipher%20which%20way%20the%20judge%20might%20be%20leaning.%20Konanur%20keeps%20things%20tense%2C%20and%20yet%20never%20makes%20the%20mistake%20of%20drawing%20attention%20to%20himself%20with%20unnecessary%20flourishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20committee%20formed%20by%20the%20principal%20comes%20to%20a%20decision%20about%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20students%2C%20two%20things%20emerge.%20The%20committee%20appears%20to%20be%20biased%20against%20Deepa%2C%20given%20how%20she%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20been%20found%20to%20be%20guilty%20of%20misdemeanours.%20They%E2%80%99re%20willing%20to%20be%20kinder%20to%20Hari%20%E2%80%93%20who%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20told%2C%20is%20good%20in%20academics%20and%20might%20hold%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20career%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20sports%20coach%20Abdul%20(Lakshmi%20Narayana)%20asks%20the%20committee%20about%20Deepa%E2%80%99s%20caste%2C%20is%20when%20things%20start%20to%20unravel.%20Abdul%20contends%20that%20if%20he%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20member%20of%20the%20committee%20belonging%20to%20a%20reserved%20category%2C%20then%20the%20optics%20of%20the%20decision%20to%20expel%20only%20Deepa%20could%20invite%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20things%20about%20Konanur%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20how%20it%20doles%20out%20empathy%20for%20everyone.%20No%20one%E2%80%99s%20a%20single-characteristic%20%E2%80%98villain%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98lover%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98teenager%E2%80%99%2C%20etc.%20Everyone%20has%20complexities%2C%20and%20strives%20to%20do%20what%20they%20consider%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98right%E2%80%99%20thing.%20Informed%20by%20their%20own%20moral%20values%2C%20they%20take%20certain%20decisions%2C%20and%20somehow%20circumstances%20spiral%20out%20of%20control.%20Many%20critics%20and%20reviews%20have%20rightly%20drawn%20parallels%20between%20Konanur%E2%80%99s%20work%20%5Bhe%20also%20directed%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EPinki%20Elli%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EWhere%20is%20Pinki%3F%3C%2Fem%3E)%5D%20and%20Asghar%20Farhadi%E2%80%99s%20films%20%E2%80%93%20where%20mundane%20details%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20the%20most%20emphatic%20reveals%20for%20the%20film.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20version%20of%20a%20domestic%20noir%2C%20where%20ordinary%20people%2C%20their%20conditioning%2C%20unreliable%20memory%20and%20moral%20uprightness%20become%20the%20ingredients%20for%20a%20thriller.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20spectacularly%20rooted%20cast%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20Jesse%20(Bhavani%20Prakash)%20who%20appears%20to%20be%20marginally%20larger-than-life.%20A%20pro-bono%20lawyer%20in%20touch%20with%20Deepa%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20she%20bursts%20into%20the%20narrative%20as%20someone%20with%20a%20saviour%20complex.%20However%2C%20the%20film%20also%20cuts%20her%20down%20to%20size%3B%20her%20activism%20turning%20a%20college%20scandal%20into%20something%20murkier%20than%20anyone%20could%20have%20probably%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EHadinelentu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20can%20feel%20Konanur%E2%80%99s%20anger%20about%20society%E2%80%99s%20many%20injustices%2C%20but%20he%20never%20lets%20rage%20get%20the%20better%20of%20him.%20In%20one%20scene%2C%20Deepa%E2%80%99s%20mother%20is%20desperately%20pleading%20with%20Hari%E2%80%99s%20mother%20to%20ensure%20that%20her%20daughter%20does%20not%20land%20in%20more%20trouble.%20She%20offers%20to%20clean%20their%20house%20every%20day%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20her%20life.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20startling%20moment%20that%20lays%20bare%20the%20tragedy%20of%20a%20country%20like%20India%3A%20where%20a%20class%20of%20citizens%20willingly%20submits%20themselves%20to%20slavery%2C%20for%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706882457000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02191734%2Fimage-1790.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fhadinelentu-prithvi-konanurs-film-on-teenagers-is-a-finely-observed-document-of-