https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F18123926%2F2022_5img17_May_2022_PTI05_17_2022_000125B-min.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Top%20Muslim%20leaders%20of%20India%20on%20Friday%20(February%202%2C%202024)%20took%20strong%20exception%20to%20the%20Varanasi%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20allowing%20Hindu%20worship%20in%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20while%20expressing%20its%20deep%20disappointment%20over%20what%20it%20believed%20was%20judicial%20backsliding%20against%20principles%20of%20justice%2C%20secularism%20and%20constitutional%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Varanasi%20Court%20Judge%20not%20only%20disregarded%20the%20plea%20of%20Muslim%20community%2C%20but%20also%20disregarded%20crores%20of%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20and%20Christians%20who%20believe%20that%20this%20country%20is%20a%20bouquet%20of%20faiths%20and%20religions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Maulana%20Khalid%20Saifullah%20Rahmani%2C%20president%20of%20All%20India%20Muslim%20Personal%20Board.%20He%20further%20said%20that%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20delivered%20a%20%E2%80%9Chasty%E2%80%9D%20judgment%2C%20overlooked%20evidence%20and%20facts%2C%20and%20refused%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20that%20prohibited%20the%20conversion%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20is%20not%20upheld%20by%20the%20Courts%2C%20we%20may%20see%20similar%20episodes%20which%20may%20trigger%20endless%20communal%20conflicts%20in%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rahmani%20raised%20an%20alarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20Muslims%20have%20played%20an%20equal%20role%20in%20securing%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%20from%20the%20British.%20But%20they%20still%20had%20to%20face%20communal%20alienation%20from%20time%20to%20time.%20However%2C%20such%20problems%20have%20accelerated%20for%20the%20community%20in%20the%20current%20times%20without%20any%20respite%20from%20the%20judiciary.%20This%20only%20makes%20us%20feel%20that%20both%20law%20and%20courts%20of%20India%20have%20become%20increasingly%20malleable%20to%20clear%20the%20majoritarian%20agenda%20of%20the%20current%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Syed%20Arshad%20Madani%2C%20President%20of%20Jamiat-Ulama-i-Hind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20handing%20over%20the%20site%20of%20(now%20demolished)%20Babri%20Masjid%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side%20has%20opened%20a%20Pandora%E2%80%99s%20Box%2C%20and%20has%20shown%20the%20way%20for%20Hindutva%20forces%20to%20stake%20claim%20on%20Muslim%20places%20of%20worship%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9COne%20has%20to%20ask%20if%20such%20is%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20how%20is%20this%20country%20going%20to%20run%20and%20prosper.%20The%20government%20has%20to%20think%20about%20which%20direction%20it%20is%20taking%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20British%20doctrine%20of%20%E2%80%9CDivide%20and%20Rule%E2%80%9D%20is%20still%20being%20practiced%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESimilarly%2C%20Malik%20Mohtasim%20Khan%20of%20Jamaat-e-Islami%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20judiciary%20and%20administration.%20The%20administration%E2%80%99s%20promptness%20to%20facilitate%20Hindu%20prayers%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20cellar%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20way%20it%20opened%20the%20barricades%20within%20hours%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Court%20had%20given%20it%20seven%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20those%20on%20the%20line%20of%20injustice%20and%20exploitation%20can%E2%80%99t%20appeal%20at%20the%20Courts%2C%20where%20should%20they%20go%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20asked%20in%20desperation%2C%20while%20talking%20about%20the%20refusal%20of%20higher%20courts%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20always%20appealed%20to%20the%20Muslim%20community%20to%20keep%20patience%20and%20maintain%20peace.%20But%20for%20how%20long%20will%20we%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%3F%20If%20Muslims%20give%20up%20on%20their%20patience%2C%20then%20it%20is%20a%20given%20that%20they%20will%20face%20damage%2C%20but%20the%20country%20will%20also%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20that%20desperation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAll%20India%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law%20Board%20official%20N.A%20Farooqui%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20our%20several%20appeals%2C%20the%20High%20Courts%20and%20Supreme%20Courts%20have%20not%20intervened%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20lower%20court%20judgements%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20fundamentally%20change%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20Muslim%20community%20is%20given%20to%20feel%20that%20even%20Courts%20are%20pandering%20to%20the%20proverb%20%E2%80%9CJiski%20Lathi%20Uski%20Bhains%E2%80%9D%20(Might%20is%20Right).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMuslim%20leaders%20condemning%20judicial%20inaction%20after%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20judgment%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20with%20their%20stance%20after%20the%202019%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20on%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%20case.%20The%20leaders%20had%20accepted%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20gracefully%2C%20while%20picking%20up%20points%20from%20the%20judgment%20that%20termed%20the%20demolition%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20as%20illegal.%20They%20had%20also%20appealed%20to%20the%20Muslim%20community%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20back-to-back%20reverses%20in%20Courts%20and%20Hindutva%20aggressive%20plans%20to%20encroach%20upon%20mosques%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20Mathura%2C%20and%20other%20towns%20have%20led%20them%20to%20condemn%20the%20judiciary%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20leaders%2C%20in%20their%20statement%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20express%20deep%20surprise%20and%20disappointment%20at%20the%20judgment%20rendered%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge.%20In%20our%20perspective%2C%20the%20decision%20seems%20to%20rely%20on%20a%20highly%20incorrect%20and%20unfounded%20argument%2C%20asserting%20that%20the%20family%20of%20Somnath%20Vyas%20used%20to%20worship%20in%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20until%201993%2C%20and%20it%20was%20closed%20on%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20orders.%20Moreover%2C%20On%20January%2024%2C%20the%20same%20court%20handed%20over%20the%20custody%20of%20the%20basement%20to%20the%20district%20administration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20pooja%20was%20ever%20conducted%20in%20this%20basement%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20judgment%20was%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Can%20absurd%20and%20baseless%20claim%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CEqually%20concerning%20is%20the%20unilateral%20disclosure%20of%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20report%20by%20the%20Hindu%20side%20to%20the%20press%2C%20causing%20turmoil%20in%20society.%20Importantly%2C%20the%20report%20is%20currently%20merely%20a%20claim%2C%20as%20it%20has%20not%20been%20discussed%20or%20confirmed%20in%20the%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20leaders%20also%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexpeditious%20execution%20of%20the%20district%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20by%20the%20administration%20was%20evidently%20aimed%20at%20undermining%20the%20right%20of%20the%20mosque%20to%20seek%20immediate%20relief%20from%20the%20High%20Court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETerming%20Courts%C2%A0%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Clast%20resort%20for%20justice%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20the%20Muslim%20leaders%20said%20that%20recent%20judgments%20indicate%20the%20makings%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajoritarian%20judiciary%E2%80%9D%2C%20even%20as%20the%20Courts%20have%20remained%20silent%20%E2%80%9Cwhile%20several%20transgressions%20of%20law%20are%20taking%20place%20at%20the%20instance%20of%20the%20Executive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20matter%20goes%20beyond%20reserving%20the%20dignity%20of%20the%20courts%3B%20it%20is%20also%20about%20safeguarding%20minority%20communities%20and%20marginalised%20sections%20from%20feeling%20deprived%20and%20frustrated%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20leaders%20said%2C%20while%20appealing%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20officials%E2%80%9D%20to%20ensure%20%E2%80%9Cimpartiality%20of%20the%20judicial%20system%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20leaders%20have%20sought%20time%20from%20the%20President%20of%20India%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20and%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D%20Y%20Chandrachud%20to%20communicate%20their%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706881566000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F18123926%2F2022_5img17_May_2022_PTI05_17_2022_000125B-min.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-order-top-muslim-leaders-condemn-courts-say-majoritarian-judiciary-in-the-making%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Condemning%20the%20judiciary%20is%20a%20first%20for%20Muslim%20leaders%2C%20and%20in%20stark%20contrast%20with%20their%20stance%20after%20the%202019%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20on%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%20case%20where%20they%20had%20appealed%20to%20the%20Muslim%20community%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20order%2C%20and%20urged%20community%20members%20to%20move%20on.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22ca