oads%2F2024%2F02%2F02175133%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-5.47.25%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nearly%20a%20year%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20directions%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20set%20to%20conduct%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20public%20hearing%20on%20human%20rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20panel%20of%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(NHRC)%20will%20hold%20%E2%80%9Ca%20Camp%20Sitting%20and%20Open%20Public%20Hearing%20on%20grievances%20of%20the%20general%20public%20regarding%20alleged%20human%20rights%20violations%20%E2%80%A6%20from%20February%207%20to%20February%209%20in%20Srinagar%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20NHRC%20notice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20asked%20people%20to%20register%20their%20complaints%20by%20January%2029%20against%20any%20public%20servant%20for%20negligence%20in%20the%20prevention%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20or%20their%20involvement%20in%20any%20such%20incident%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20a%20recurrent%20theme%20in%20the%20five%20years%20of%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20rule%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20will%20be%20taken%20up%20at%20the%20official%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDays%20after%20civilians%E2%80%99%20custodial%20killing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NHRC%20hearing%20will%20take%20place%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20shocking%20incident%20in%20Poonch%20district%20in%20which%20three%20civilians%20were%20allegedly%20tortured%20to%20death%20in%20Army%20custody%20in%20December%20last%20year%20while%20at%20least%20four%20others%20were%20grievously%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202020%2C%20the%20Union%20had%20empowered%20the%20NHRC%20to%20handle%20the%20human%20rights%20concerns%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20But%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20its%20local%20offices%2C%20there%20is%20no%20information%20whether%20the%20commission%20took%20cognisance%20of%20any%20case%20over%20the%20last%20more%20than%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(SHRC)%2C%20a%20quasi-judicial%20body%20that%20investigated%20rights%20abuses%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20ceased%20to%20exist%20on%20October%2031%2C%202019%2C%20when%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%20came%20into%20effect%20and%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20was%20divided%20into%20two%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20legislations%2C%20including%20J%26amp%3BK%20Protection%20of%20Human%20Rights%20Act%2C%201997%20that%20formed%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20the%20SHRC%2C%20were%20repealed%20after%20the%20Reorganisation%20Act%20became%20applicable%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpoonch-civilians-killed-are-among-the-men-seen-in-video-being-tortured-by-soldiers-sarpanch-confirms%5C%22%3EPoonch%20Civilians%20Killed%20Are%20Among%20the%20Men%20Seen%20in%20Video%20Being%20Tortured%20By%20Soldiers%2C%20Sarpanch%20Confirms%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20a%20petition%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20a%20Pune-based%20lawyer%20Asim%20Suhas%20Sarode%20about%20the%20absence%20of%20statutory%20bodies%2C%20including%20human%20rights%20commission%2C%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20after%20it%20was%20downgraded%20into%20a%20union%20territory%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Centre%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20defunct%20human%20rights%20commission%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20under%20its%20consideration.%20Later%2C%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20bring%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmechanism%20which%20will%20allow%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20file%20their%20complaints%20to%20the%20NHRC%20from%20J%26amp%3BK%20itself%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh%20official%20figures%2C%20higher%20unofficial%20numbers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SHRC%20was%20probing%20at%20least%20630%20complaints%20of%20murder%2C%20enforced%20disappearances%2C%20rape%2C%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20abuses%20allegedly%20perpetrated%20by%20security%20forces%20on%20local%20residents%2C%20according%20to%20official%20data%20accessed%20by%20an%20RTI%20activist%2C%20when%20it%20was%20shut%20down%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20records%20of%20the%20commission%20were%20locked%20in%20a%20designated%20room%20at%20the%20office%20premises%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%2C%20Old%20Assembly%20Complex%2C%20Srinagar%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20administration%20said%20in%20its%20reply%20to%20the%20RTI%20by%20activist%20Venkatesh%20Nayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20unofficial%20figures%20are%20much%20higher.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Farchive%2Fin%2Fentry%2Fkashmir-human-rights-commission_in_5de7e7e8e4b0913e6f898743%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHuffpost%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20quoting%20the%20annual%20report%20of%20the%20SHRC%20for%20the%20year%202017-18%2C%20more%20than%208%2C000%20cases%20of%20abuses%2C%20including%20torture%2C%20disappearances%2C%20extra-judicial%20killings%2C%20harassment%20and%20others%20were%20pending%20with%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20UN%20panel%20had%20rapped%20the%20Centre%20in%20September%202020%20over%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20SHRC%20while%20calling%20for%20investigation%20into%20enforced%20disappearance%20and%20mass%20graves%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20According%20to%20independent%20estimates%2C%20more%20than%208000%20people%20have%20become%20victims%20of%20enforced%20disappearance%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20since%20the%20insurgency%20erupted%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvestigations%20%E2%80%98penalised%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Khurram%20Pervez%2C%20the%20convenor%20of%20Coalition%20of%20Civil%20Society%20(CCS)%2C%20a%20conglomerate%20of%20human%20rights%20groups%20and%20individuals%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20documenting%20the%20rights%20abuses%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20involvement%20in%20%E2%80%9Cterror%20funding%E2%80%9D%20and%20arrested%20by%20the%20National%20Investigations%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20inception%20in%202000%2C%20the%20CCS%20has%20published%20dozens%20of%20annual%2C%20biyearly%20and%20special%20reports%20on%20human%20rights%20abuses%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20involving%20security%20forces%20as%20well%20as%20militants.%20However%2C%20after%20the%20arrest%20of%20its%20convenor%2C%20the%20group%20has%20become%20defunct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CCS%E2%80%99s%20last%20report%20was%20about%20the%20three%20youth%20from%20Rajouri%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20staged%20gun-battle%20by%20the%20Army%20in%202020%2C%20a%20year%20after%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20was%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20while%20hearing%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20recommended%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Committee%E2%80%99%20to%20investigate%20the%20rights%20abuses%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20will%20investigate%20and%20report%20on%20the%20violations%20of%20human%20rights%20perpetrated%20both%20by%20the%20State%20and%20non-state%20actors%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20at%20least%20since%20the%201980s%20and%20recommend%20measures%20for%20reconciliation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20that%20heard%20the%20matter%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20already%20an%20entire%20generation%20of%20youth%20that%20has%20grown%20up%20with%20a%20feeling%20of%20distrust%20and%20it%20is%20to%20them%20that%20we%20owe%20the%20greatest%20day%20of%20liberation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706876587000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02175133%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-5.47.25%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnhrc-supreme-court-kashmir-human-rights%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20a%20recurrent%20theme%20in%20the%20five%20years%20of%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20rule%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20will%20be%20taken%20up%20at%20the%20official%20level.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnhrc-supreme-court-kashmir-human-rights%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Immediate%20HC%20Relief%2C%20Puja%20to%20Continue%20Inside%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20Basement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F23142008%2FGyan-vapi-mosque-min.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Hindu%20prayers%20inside%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20in%20Varanasi%20will%20continue%20at%20least%20till%20February%206%2C%20as%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20on%20Friday%20(February%202)%20did%20not%20grant%20any%20relief%20to%20the%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20who%20were%20seeking%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20district%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20handing%20the%20basement%20over%20to%20Hindus%20for%20%3Cem%3Epuja%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20directed%20the%20management%20committee%20of%20the%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masajid%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%2C%20to%20file%20a%20fresh%2C%20amended%20appeal%20against%20the%20district%20court%20order%20and%20said%20it%20would%20hear%20the%20matter%20on%20February%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Rohit%20Ranjan%20Agarwal%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20directed%20the%20state%20government%20to%20maintain%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation.%20Ajay%20Mishra%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20advocate%20general%2C%20committed%20to%20the%20court%20that%20the%20district%20magistrate%20would%20do%20so%20%E2%80%9Cpursuant%20to%20the%20order%20passed%20by%20the%E2%80%9D%20Varanasi%20district%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20management%20committee%20had%20approached%20the%20high%20court%20on%20January%2031%2C%20challenging%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court%20order%20and%20its%20subsequent%20compliance%20within%20half%20a%20day%20by%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20allow%20Hindu%20prayers%20inside%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20basement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20sought%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20puja%20being%20conducted%20inside%20the%20basement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Hasty%E2%80%99%20implementation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid-Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20matter%20raised%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprimary%20objection%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20maintainability%20of%20the%20appeal%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20the%20basic%20order%20of%20January%2017%2C%20which%20preceded%20the%20eventual%20handing%20over%20of%20the%20basement%2C%20had%20not%20been%20challenged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20administration%20had%20on%20January%2024%20completed%20the%20process%20of%20taking%20over%20the%20basement%20after%20the%20district%20court%20on%20January%2017%20directed%20the%20district%20magistrate%20to%20keep%20the%20cellar%20secure%20and%20appointed%20him%20as%20its%20receiver.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20asked%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20mosque%20management%20committee%20why%20they%20had%20not%20challenged%20the%20January%2017%20order%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20S.F.A.%20Naqvi%2C%20arguing%20for%20the%20mosque%20management%20committee%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20they%20would%20file%20an%20amended%20application%20challenging%20the%20order%20dated%20January%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20committee%20criticised%20the%20district%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20and%20its%20%E2%80%9Chasty%E2%80%9D%20implementation%20by%20the%20district%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20Friday%20prayers%2C%20it%20appealed%20to%20all%20Muslims%20in%20Varanasi%20to%20keep%20their%20shops%20and%20business%20establishments%20shut%20on%20Friday%20(February%202)%20from%20the%20afternoon%20prayers%20till%20%3Cem%3Easar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(early%20evening%20prayers).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EState%20police%20beefed%20up%20security%20in%20the%20city%2C%20around%20the%20mosque%20and%20in%20Muslim%20localities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funderstanding-the-gyanvapi-mosque-dispute-what-does-the-places-of-worship-act-say%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Case%3A%20What%20Does%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Say%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELocal%20strike%20a%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaulana%20Abdul%20Batin%20Nomani%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20mosque%20management%20committee%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebandh%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Csuccess%E2%80%9D%20as%20shops%20in%20the%20Muslim-populated%20localities%20remained%20shut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENomani%20said%20that%20the%20Friday%20namaz%20was%20held%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20in%20a%20peaceful%20manner%20and%20that%20attendance%20was%20higher%20than%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20%3Cem%3Emajma%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bcongregation%5D%20was%20larger%20than%20usual.%20Police%20did%20stop%20people%20from%20entering%20the%20mosque%20complex%2C%20but%20only%20after%20it%20had%20reached%20peak%20capacity%20and%20even%20more.%20When%20there%20were%20no%20more%20possibilities%20to%20accommodate%20more%20namazis%2C%20around%201%2C500%20persons%20had%20to%20return%20%5Bwithout%20offering%20namaz%20there%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20day%20after%20the%20district%20court%20controversially%20allowed%20Hindus%20to%20conduct%20puja%20inside%20a%20basement%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%2C%20the%20Varanasi%20administration%20in%20Adityanath-ruled%20UP%20moved%20swiftly%20to%20arrange%20prayer%20rituals%20by%20a%20Hindu%20priest%20inside%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20basement%20in%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20February%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20administration%20and%20police%20stepped%20in%20to%20secure%20the%20area%20late%20at%20night%20and%20removed%20the%20barricading%20on%20the%20southern%20end%20of%20the%20mosque%20just%20hours%20after%20district%20judge%20Ajaya%20Krishna%20Vishvesha%20on%20January%2031%20%E2%80%93%20his%20last%20working%20day%20before%20retirement%20%E2%80%93%20allowed%20Hindus%20to%20worship%20in%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20sealed%20basement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20had%20been%20barricaded%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20in%20December%201993%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%E2%80%99s%20demolition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EClaims%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20management%20committee%20has%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20and%20baseless%E2%80%9D%20the%20claims%20by%20a%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20that%20idols%20of%20Hindu%20deities%20were%20kept%20inside%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20mosque%20and%20that%20they%20used%20to%20be%20worshipped%20by%20his%20ancestors%20till%20the%20mosque%20was%20barricaded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENomani%20said%20that%20while%20the%20district%20court%20had%20given%20the%20administration%20seven%20days%20to%20arrange%20for%20puja%20inside%20the%20basement%2C%20the%20officials%20did%20not%20even%20wait%20for%20%E2%80%9Cseven%20hours%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20did%20it%20in%20supreme%20haste.%20The%20reason%20why%20they%20did%20it%20was%20because%20once%20the%20puja%20starts%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20stop%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nomani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVishnu%20Shankar%20Jain%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%2C%20had%20on%20Thursday%20said%20that%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court%20had%20been%20complied%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Cem%3Epujari%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Mandir%20Trust%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%2C%20conducted%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eshayan%20aarti%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20after%20%E2%80%9Cputting%20up%20idols%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20basement%2C%20said%20Jain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAn%20%3Cem%3Eakhand%20jyoti%3C%2Fem%3E%20started%20in%20front%20of%20them.%20Daily%20aarti%20of%20all%20the%20above%20deities%20%E2%80%93%20morning%20%3Cem%3Emangla%3C%2Fem%3E%20aarti%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebhog%3C%2Fem%3E%20aarti%2C%20evening%20aarti%2C%20late%20sunset%20evening%20aarti%2C%20shayan%20aarti%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Vishvesha%20on%20January%2031%20directed%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20arrangements%20for%20puja%20and%20other%20Hindu%20activities%20inside%20the%20southern%20%3Cem%3Etehkhana%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cellar)%20of%20the%20mosque%20within%20seven%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20directed%20the%20administration%20to%20conduct%20the%20puja%20and%20%E2%80%9Crag-bhog%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cidols%E2%80%9D%20inside%20the%20tehkhana%20through%20a%20pujari%20appointed%20by%20the%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fkashi-mathura-baaki-hain-why-the-ayodhya-verdict-wont-offer-any-respite-from-saffron-hatred%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Kashi-Mathura%20Baaqi%20Hain%E2%80%99%3A%20Why%20the%20Ayodhya%20Verdict%20Won%E2%80%99t%20Offer%20Any%20Respite%20From%20Saffron%20Hatred%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20survey%20and%20idols%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Varanasi%20court%20order%20came%20days%20after%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20in%20its%20survey%20report%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20claimed%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20Hindu%20temple%E2%80%9D%20existed%20there%20prior%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20existing%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%2C%20the%20mosque%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20temple%20were%20modified%20and%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Islamic%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20committee%20is%20yet%20to%20submit%20a%20detailed%20objection%20to%20the%20report%20but%20has%20disagreed%20with%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20on%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20a%20local%20priest%2C%20Shailendra%20Kumar%20Pathak%2C%20of%20the%20Acharya%20Ved%20Vyas%20Peeth%20temple%2C%20who%20had%20sought%20rights%20to%20worship%20the%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20and%20other%20alleged%20visible%20and%20invisible%20deities%20he%20claimed%20were%20in%20the%20cellar%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20rejected%20all%20claims%20made%20by%20Pathak%20that%20there%20were%20idols%20kept%20inside%20the%20previously%20sealed%20cellar%20and%20that%20his%20ancestors%20used%20to%20carry%20out%20puja%20inside%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Vishvesha%2C%20however%2C%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20and%20directed%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20necessary%20iron%20fencing%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20puja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPathak%20also%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9CPujari%20Vyas%20ji%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20Somnath%20Vyas%2C%20his%20maternal%20grandfather%2C%20was%20prevented%20from%20entering%20the%20barricaded%20area%20of%20the%20mosque%20after%20December%201993.%20The%20rag-bhog%20and%20%3Cem%3Esanskar%3C%2Fem%3E%20rituals%20were%20also%20stopped%2C%20Pathak%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20ancient%20Hindu%20idols%20and%20several%20other%20religious%20items%20linked%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religion%20were%20inside%20the%20cellar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20carry%20out%20regular%20puja%20of%20the%20murtis%20%5Bidols%5D%20inside%20the%20tehkhana%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20management%20committee%20denied%20the%20claims%20in%20court.%20The%20committee%20in%20written%20applications%20told%20the%20court%20that%20no%20member%20of%20the%20Vyas%20family%20ever%20carried%20out%20puja%20in%20the%20cellar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20question%20of%20stopping%20someone%20from%20conducting%20puja%20from%20December%201993%20does%20not%20arise%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98All%20lies%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20alleged%20idol%20was%20ever%20present%20at%20the%20site%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20committee%20said%20and%20denied%20the%20claims%20of%20Pathak%20that%20his%20family%20had%20ancestral%20occupation%20of%20the%20cellar.%20The%20cellar%20has%20always%20been%20under%20the%20occupation%20of%20the%20mosque%20committee%2C%20the%20caretakers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.M.%20Yasin%2C%20joint%20secretary%20of%20the%20mosque%20committee%2C%20rejected%20the%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20temple%20side%20and%20said%20that%20no%20puja%20had%20ever%20been%20held%20in%20the%20tehkhana%20and%20that%20there%20are%20no%20idols%20there.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20only%20bamboo%20poles%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20all%20lies.%20They%20have%20no%20evidence.%20The%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20without%20any%20evidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yasin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYasin%20also%20questioned%20why%20the%20judge%20did%20not%20seek%20a%20factual%20position%20from%20the%20district%20administration%2C%20which%20had%20sealed%20the%20cellar%20and%20barricaded%20the%20premises%20in%201995%20on%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cellar%20has%20always%20been%20in%20our%20possession%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yasin%2C%20who%20objected%20to%20the%20breach%20of%20the%20old%20barricade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20of%20the%20mosque%20side%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Deen%20Mohammad%20suit%20of%201937%20did%20not%20make%20any%20mention%20of%20Vyas%20family%20occupying%20the%20tehkhana.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706876176000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F23142008%2FGyan-vapi-mosque-min.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpuja-to-continue-in-gyanvapi-basement-no-hc-relief-feb-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20asked%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque's%20management%20committee%20why%20they%20had%20not%20challenged%20the%20January%2017%20order%20%E2%80%93%20which%20preceded%20the%20eventual%20handing%20over%20of%20the%20mosque's%20basement%20%E2%80%93%20first.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpuja-to-continue-in-gyanvapi-basement-no-hc-relief-feb-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22French%20farmers%20lift%20road%20blockades%20around%20Paris%20after%20the%20prime%20minister%20offers%20a%20support%20plan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706876174000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22h