%20Kumbh%20Mela.%20On%20February%204%2C%202019%2C%20over%2024%20crore%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-record-over-24-crore-people-visited-kumbh-2019-more-than-total-tourists-in-up-in-2014-17%2Fstory-9uncpmhBPnBj11ClnTiYQP.html%5C%22%3Eattended%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Ardh%20Kumbh%20Mela%20at%20Prayagraj%2C%20marking%20the%20highest%20attendance%20ever%20on%20a%20single%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kumbh%20Mela%20stands%20as%20a%20breathtaking%20testament%20to%20mass%20faith%20in%20practice%2C%20spanning%20centuries.%20Its%20roots%20extend%20back%20to%20ancient%20times%2C%20with%20mentions%20in%20the%20Rig%20Veda%20(1500%20BCE)%20and%20early%20Puranas.%20In%20644%20CE%2C%20the%20Buddhist%20Chinese%20traveler%20Hiuen%20Tsang%2C%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20King%20Harsha%E2%80%99s%20Prayag%2C%20provided%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Kumbh%20Mela.%20Abul%20Fazl%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Ain-i-Akbari%2C%E2%80%99%20written%20in%201590%2C%20also%20details%20the%20Kumbha%20or%20Magha%20Mela%2C%20as%20it%20was%20commonly%20referred%20to%20then.%20Munshi%20Sujan%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKhulasat-ut-Tawarikh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20written%20in%201695%2C%20chronicles%20multiple%20Kumbh%20Melas%20at%20Haridwar%2C%20Trimbak%20(near%20Nashik%2C%20at%20the%20source%20of%20the%20Godavari%20River)%2C%20and%20Prayag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20crores%20of%20Hindus%20have%20actively%20participated%20in%20the%20Kumbh%20Melas.%20This%20tradition%20did%20not%20halt%20or%20stutter%20even%20during%20the%20years%20of%20Mughal%20rule%20and%20the%20British%20Raj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fa-lesson-on-temples-from-swami-vivekananda%5C%22%3EA%20Lesson%20on%20Temples%20From%20Swami%20Vivekananda%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20Mandir%20inauguration%2C%20a%20political%20event%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ram%20Mandir%20campaign%2C%20the%20build%20up%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20intertwining%20of%20it%20with%20the%20Modi%20cult%2C%20the%20raucous%20nature%20of%20it%2C%20the%20merchandising%20of%20it%2C%20the%20face-paint%2C%20the%20flags%2C%20the%20roping%20in%20of%20Bollywood%20celebs%20as%20amplifiers%20of%20the%20event%20%E2%80%93%20made%20it%20far%20more%20similar%20to%20a%20jamboree%20like%20the%20Indian%20Premier%20League.%20A%20new%20mandir%20does%20not%20need%20the%20build-up%20that%20comes%20before%20a%20major%20Bollywood%20film.%20So%20why%20were%20we%20subjected%20to%20all%20the%20hype%3F%20Because%2C%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20was%20a%20political%20event.%20It%20was%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20political%20campaign%20that%20had%20to%20be%20seriously%20played%20up.%20And%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20quick%20uttering%20of%20the%20Gayatri%20Mantra%20at%20home%2C%20my%20visit%20to%20the%20neighbourhood%20mandir%2C%20my%20trip%20to%20Haridwar%20with%20the%20ashes%20of%20my%20grandparent%2C%20even%20mass%20events%20like%20the%20Kumbh%2C%20or%20the%20daily%20churn%20of%20the%20faithful%20that%20we%20see%20on%20the%20ghats%20of%20Varanasi%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20are%20deeply%20personal%20spiritual%20acts%20and%20journeys%2C%20for%20all%20practicing%20Hindus.%20It%20does%20not%20require%20hype%20to%20urge%20me%20or%20any%20other%20Hindu%20to%20do%20any%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20also%20examine%20the%20argument%20about%20how%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20will%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99%20the%20Hindu%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20already%20described%20how%20Hindus%20have%20steadily%20practiced%20their%20faith%20over%20the%20centuries%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20medieval%20despot%20who%20ran%20their%20lives%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20some%20kind%2C%20some%20cruel%2C%20some%20self-serving%2C%20Hindu%2C%20Christian%20and%20Muslim%20alike.%20For%20most%20Hindus%2C%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20their%20religion%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20need%20any%20decolonising%20when%20India%20achieved%20independence%20in%201947.%20There%20was%20no%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98religious%20inferiority%E2%80%99%20to%20shrug%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20Satyagraha%20%E2%80%98decolonised%E2%80%99%20the%20Indian%20mind%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20needed%20was%20mass%20political%20emancipation%2C%20and%20in%20the%2030%20years%20preceding%201947%2C%20that%20push%20came%20from%20Gandhi.%20His%20unique%20mobilisation%20of%20crores%20of%20Indians%20to%20participate%20in%20non-violent%20protest%20and%20resistance%20made%20each%20of%20them%20a%20stakeholder%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20facilitated%20a%20mass%20shedding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20mindset.%20Thousands%20of%20freedom%20fighters%20went%20to%20jail%2C%20hundreds%20were%20beaten%20in%20lathi%20charges%2C%20and%20hundreds%20were%20killed%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unprecedented%20number%20of%20Indians%20were%20invested%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%2C%20and%20they%20remained%20invested%20even%20after%20August%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20mind%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20our%20fledgling%20democracy%20did%20not%20unravel%20like%20that%20of%20many%20countries%20that%20emerged%20from%20colonialism.%20A%20young%20nation%20would%20not%20have%20grown%20from%20strength%20to%20strength%20as%20a%20democracy%20if%20it%20had%20not%20decisively%20broken%20away%20from%20its%20colonial%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20break%20away%20from%20is%20not%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98colonial%E2%80%99%20past%2C%20but%20its%20post-colonial%20%E2%80%98Nehruvian%E2%80%99%20past.%20The%20aversion%20to%20Nehru%2C%20and%20a%20more%20discreet%20aversion%20to%20Gandhi%2C%20is%20present%20simply%20because%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20need%20to%20%E2%80%98clear%20the%20shelf%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20earlier%20icons%20and%20make%20room%20for%20their%20own.%20But%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20that%20without%20attacking%20them%20and%20their%20contributions%20and%20accusing%20them%20of%20failing%20to%20rid%20India%20of%20its%20%E2%80%98colonial%20mindset.%E2%80%99%20India%20did%20shed%20its%20British%20past%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%2C%20in%20mind%2C%20spirit%2C%20and%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20Once%20There%20Was%20a%20Mosque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98superpower%E2%80%99%20moment%20came%20before%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20sounding%20a%20bit%20simplistically%20ra-ra-ish%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20ask%3A%20Did%20India%20wait%20for%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20before%20becoming%20a%20nuclear%20power%20complete%20with%20warheads%3F%20Did%20India%20need%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20to%20motivate%20it%20to%20become%20a%20leader%20in%20space%20exploration%20or%20to%20have%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20defence%20forces%3F%20Did%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20propel%20India%20to%20become%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%3F%20For%20decades%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20massive%20%E2%80%98soft%E2%80%99%20power%20has%20grown%20organically%20(unlike%20the%20heavily%20%E2%80%98marketed%E2%80%99%20soft%20power%20of%20the%20US)%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20diaspora%2C%20its%20cinema%2C%20its%20cricket%2C%20its%20food%2C%20its%20music%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20India%20does%20not%20need%20to%20shake%20off%20any%20imaginary%20vestiges%20of%20any%20imaginary%20colonial%20hangover.%20It%20was%20all%20done%20and%20dusted%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20call%20out%20the%20%E2%80%98pseudo-religious%E2%80%99%20nature%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20political%20campaign%20and%20understand%20it%20for%20what%20it%20really%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frohit-khanna%5C%22%3ERohit%20Khanna%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20video%20storyteller.%20He%20has%20been%20managing%20editor%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Quint%3Cem%3E%2C%20and%20is%20a%20two-time%20Ramnath%20Goenka%20Award%20winner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706874802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22185025%2FScreenshot-2024-01-22-at-12.41.27-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindus-havent-lost-their-way-unveiling-the-pseudo-religiosity-behind-the-ram-mandir-campaign%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20as%20intrinsically%20Hindu%20is%20the%20long%20trek%20to%20the%20Amarnath%20cave%20or%20Kedarnath%20or%20Gangotri%20Dham%2C%20or%20to%20the%20Vaishno%20Devi%20mandir.%20The%20devotees%20may%20well%20add%20the%20new%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Mandir%20to%20their%20bucket%20list%2C%20but%20it%20won't%20make%20them%20any%20more%20Hindu%20than%20they%20already%20are.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindus-havent-lost-their-way-unveiling-the-pseudo-religiosity-behind-the-ram-mandir-campaign%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Making%20Sense%20of%20'Ethical%20Violence'%20and%20'Defensive%20Wars'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07173950%2Fimage1170x530cropped-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20title%20suggests%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transcript-publishing.com%2Fauthor%2Fbordoni-carlo-320001319%2F%5C%22%3ECarlo%20Bordini%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wiley.com%2Fen-us%2FEthical%2BViolence-p-9781509561032%5C%22%3EEthical%20Violence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20studies%20the%20ways%20different%20forms%20of%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20but%20not%20only%2C%20war%20%E2%80%93%20come%20to%20be%20accepted%20as%20morally%20legitimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20builds%20on%20the%20Italian%20sociologist%20and%20journalist%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thriftbooks.com%2Fa%2Fcarlo-bordoni%2F1772601%2F%5C%22%3Eprior%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20examining%20social%20forces%20and%20changes%20unfolding%20in%20modern%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Bordoni%2C%20%E2%80%9Cethical%20violence%E2%80%9D%20is%20violence%20that%2C%20though%20dangerous%2C%20has%20become%20legitimised%20and%20accepted%20by%20a%20community%20as%20permissible%20or%20even%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%20explores%20the%20horrors%20of%20Nazi%20Germany%20and%20considers%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20While%20the%20book%20does%20not%20touch%20on%20the%20current%20conflagrations%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20these%20provide%20all-too-clear%20examples%20of%20brutality%20that%20is%20accepted%20and%20even%20celebrated%20by%20different%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20basic%20moral%20tenet%20and%20enduring%20concept%20in%20ethics%20that%20life%20is%20sacred%20and%20worthy%20of%20respect.%20So%20how%20might%20the%20known%2C%20intentional%20killing%20of%20thousands%20of%20human%20beings%2C%20such%20as%20in%20a%20war%2C%20be%20morally%20accepted%3F%20Or%20even%20seen%20as%20rational%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%20surveys%20a%20myriad%20of%20hypotheses%2C%20traversing%20sociology%2C%20philosophy%2C%20political%20theory%2C%20history%2C%20legal%20theory%2C%20and%20the%20social%20sciences.%20He%20brings%20into%20discussion%20thinkers%20as%20diverse%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fexplainer-nietzsche-nihilism-and-reasons-to-be-cheerful-130378%5C%22%3EFriedrich%20Nietzsche%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplato.stanford.edu%2Fentries%2Fweber%2F%5C%22%3EMax%20Weber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fexplainer-the-ideas-of-foucault-99758%5C%22%3EMichel%20Foucault%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FCarl_Schmitt%5C%22%3ECarl%20Schmitt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplato.stanford.edu%2Fentries%2Farendt%2F%5C%22%3EHannah%20Arendt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstevenpinker.com%2F%5C%22%3ESteven%20Pinker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FZygmunt-Bauman%5C%22%3EZygmunt%20Bauman%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20sociologist%20Weber%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20viewed%20war%20as%20a%20beneficial%20catalyst%20for%20change.%20German%20philosopher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FGeorg-Simmel%5C%22%3EGeorg%20Simmel%3C%2Fa%3E%20speculated%20on%20war%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20create%20valuable%20internal%20cohesion%20among%20nation-states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESifting%20through%20various%20views%2C%20Bordoni%20reflects%20that%20even%20in%20a%20single%20case%20there%20may%20be%20multiple%20answers.%20Leaders%20may%20have%20rational%20reasons%20(moral%20or%20self-interested)%20for%20going%20to%20war.%20Yet%20solidarity%2C%20heightened%20emotion%20and%20even%20irrationality%20might%20also%20be%20required%20to%20ignite%20the%20popular%20will%20to%20wage%20war%2C%20with%20all%20its%20sacrifices%20and%20brutalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESelf-defence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20late%2020th%20century%20saw%20the%20fitful%20development%20of%20the%20view%20that%20wars%20must%20not%20be%20fought%20for%20a%20state%E2%80%99s%20general%20political%20or%20economic%20interests%2C%20but%20only%20in%20self-defence.%20As%20Bordoni%20observes%2C%20this%20shut%20the%20front%20door%20to%20war%20only%20to%20allow%20it%20in%20through%20the%20back.%20Today%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20have%20defensive%20wars.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20conflagrations%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20support%20Bordoni%E2%80%99s%20insight.%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Yemen%2C%20Iran%20and%20Pakistan%3A%20all%20these%20very%20different%20conflicts%20are%2C%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20those%20fighting%20them%2C%20defensive%20wars.%20Each%20side%20sees%20itself%20as%20justifiably%20responding%20to%20a%20past%20or%20present%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20Russia%20dubiously%20justified%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20by%20claiming%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.france24.com%2Fen%2Flive-news%2F20230127-putin-blasts-neo-nazis-in-ukraine-on-holocaust-remembrance-day%5C%22%3Edefending%20citizens%20against%20%E2%80%9CNazis%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20describing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2022%2Ffeb%2F28%2Fnato-expansion-war-russia-ukraine%5C%22%3ENATO%E2%80%99s%20expansion%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20serious%20provocation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%20960w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722-300x203.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-636960%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22649%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20photo%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier.%20Photo%3A%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%E2%80%99s%20work%20helps%20us%20understand%20the%20many%20reasons%20why%20societies%20might%20adopt%20a%20war%20footing.%20It%20is%20less%20useful%2C%20though%2C%20in%20trying%20to%20think%20through%20the%20ethics%20of%20these%20conflicts%2C%20if%20by%20ethics%20we%20mean%20what%20we%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%20suggests%20that%20if%20we%20truly%20acknowledged%20the%20ethical%20value%20of%20all%20human%20life%20(including%20that%20of%20our%20enemies)%2C%20war%20would%20not%20be%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20draws%20on%20Judith%20Butler%E2%80%99s%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fblogs%2Fnews%2F2339-judith-butler-precariousness-and-grievability%5C%22%3Egrievability%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20where%20communities%20determine%20whose%20deaths%20are%20appropriately%20mourned.%20Some%20lives%20will%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20valued%20and%20their%20deaths%20not%20worthy%20of%20grieving.%20If%20all%20lives%20were%20recognised%20as%20grievable%2C%20Bordoni%20argues%2C%20it%20would%20be%20impossible%20to%20accept%20war%E2%80%99s%20human%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Bordoni%E2%80%99s%20argument%20here%20seems%20flawed%20on%20two%20important%20counts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20is%20not%20necessary%20to%20dehumanise%20someone%20to%20decide%20they%20must%20be%20killed.%20It%20is%20entirely%20possible%20to%20cleave%20to%20a%20moral%20principle%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20everyone%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20life%20%E2%80%93%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25482401%5C%22%3Eneutralise%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20principle%E2%80%99s%20applicability%20in%20the%20present%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20done%20in%20selective%20and%20hypocritical%20ways.%20Our%20ingenious%20human%20brains%20can%20confect%20reasons%20why%20this%20case%20is%20an%20exception%20to%20a%20rule%20we%20otherwise%20righteously%20acknowledge.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20presents%20a%20plausible%20example.%20Russia%20never%20claimed%20state%20sovereignty%20was%20meaningless%20or%20Ukrainian%20citizens%20deserve%20to%20be%20slaughtered.%20Instead%2C%20its%20claims%20about%20Nazis%20and%20NATO%20sought%20to%20show%20the%20Ukrainian%20context%20created%20an%20exception%20to%20the%20widely%20accepted%20prohibition%20on%20military%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20there%20is%20one%20case%20where%20that%20%E2%80%9Cexception%E2%80%9D%20does%20seem%20justified%2C%20namely%2C%20in%20genuine%20cases%20of%20self-defence.%20Most%20contemporary%20ethical%20thought%20%E2%80%93%20in%20particular%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiep.utm.edu%2Fjustwar%2F%5C%22%3Ejust%20war%20theory%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20allows%20the%20use%20of%20war%2C%20and%20even%20collateral%20damage%2C%20in%20self%20defence%20against%20aggressors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20important%20point%3A%20%E2%80%9Cethical%20violence%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20sociological%20process%20of%20building%20popular%20legitimacy%20for%20mass%20violence%20(Bordoni%E2%80%99s%20focus).%20It%20is%20also%20the%20demand%20to%20temper%20our%20violence%20until%20it%20can%20pass%20ethical%20muster.%20This%20involves%20providing%20strictures%20on%20when%20actions%20like%20war%20are%20permissible%20(the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fdocument%2Fwhat-are-jus-ad-bellum-and-jus-bello-0%25EF%25BB%25BF%5C%22%3Ejus%20ad%20bellum%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20just%20war%20theory).%20It%20also%20requires%20respecting%20laws%20like%20the%20Geneva%20Conventions%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fsouth-africa-has-made-its-genocide-case-against-israel-in-court-heres-what-both-sides-said-and-what-happens-next-221017%5C%22%3EGenocide%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20protect%20civilians%20during%20war%20(the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fwar-and-law%2Fihl-other-legal-regmies%2Fjus-in-bello-jus-ad-bellum%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DInternational%2520humanitarian%2520law%252C%2520or%2520jus%2CRead%2520more%5C%22%3Ejus%20in%20bello%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20counterargument%20here%20is%20that%2C%20while%20genuine%20claims%20of%20self-defence%20are%20pivotal%20in%20ethical%20decisions%20to%20visit%20violence%20on%20others%2C%20it%20may%20be%20that%20the%20social%20and%20psychological%20weight%20of%20actually%20inflicting%20the%20brutal%20violence%20demanded%20by%20war%20requires%20a%20dehumanised%20and%20hated%20foe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20is%20the%20case%2C%20even%20the%20most%20justified%20war%20carries%20a%20profound%20moral%20risk.%20We%20must%20demean%20the%20enemy%2C%20seeing%20human%20beings%20as%20obstacles%20requiring%20elimination%2C%20rather%20than%20intrinsic%20sources%20of%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EModernity%20and%20mass%20violence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20is%20it%20that%20modernity%20%E2%80%93%20since%20the%20Enlightenment%20%E2%80%93%20has%20not%20consigned%20war%20and%20terrorism%20to%20the%20barbaric%20past%3F%20Bordoni%20develops%20a%20complex%20picture%20of%20modernity%20%E2%80%93%20or%20rather%20%3Cem%3Emodernities%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20following%20Israeli%20sociologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FMultiple-Modernities%2FEisenstadt%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780765809261%5C%22%3EShmuel%20Eisenstadt%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20seeing%20a%20series%20of%20sociological%20and%20economic%20upheavals%20over%20recent%20centuries.%20These%20included%20the%20creation%20of%20state%20sovereignty%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20reason%20and%20science%2C%20industrialisation%20and%20the%20proliferation%20of%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20these%20we%20must%20add%20the%20crises%20of%20modernity%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20with%20its%20values%20of%20progress%2C%20human%20equality%20and%20rationality%20being%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%20sees%20our%20current%20times%20as%20characterised%20by%20a%20pushback%20against%20rationality%20and%20science%2C%20with%20the%20embrace%20of%20emotions%20(including%20resentment).%20We%20take%20rationality%20for%20granted%2C%20he%20warns%2C%20but%20in%20truth%2C%20it%20is%20a%20cultural%20achievement%20%E2%80%93%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprecious%20plant%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20Bordoni%20cautions%20against%20the%20comfortable%20view%20the%20excesses%20of%2020th%20century%20violence%20were%20departures%20from%20modernity.%20For%20modernity%20promises%20an%20orderly%2C%20standardised%20world%2C%20governed%20and%20controlled%20by%20precise%20rules%20to%20achieve%20conformity%2C%20security%2C%20safety%20and%20prosperity.%20This%20demand%20for%20control%20and%20perfection%20characterises%20the%20totalitarian%20impulse.%20Totalitarianism%20inevitably%20produces%20enormous%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20intellectually%20refreshing%20in%20its%20willingness%20to%20marshal%20many%20different%20ideas%20and%20to%20resist%20definitively%20choosing%20one%20theory%20or%20approach%20over%20another.%20But%20this%20very%20feature%20can%20make%20%3Cem%3EEthical%20Violence%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20challenging%20and%20at%20times%20frustrating%20read.%20The%20book%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20central%20driving%20thesis%20or%20overarching%20argument%20the%20author%20systematically%20pursues.%20Many%20ideas%20are%20raised%2C%20briefly%20discussed%2C%20then%20left%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBordoni%E2%80%99s%20sociological%20and%20historical%20approach%20helps%20the%20reader%20stand%20back%20from%20the%20headlines%20to%20consider%20the%20modern%20world%E2%80%99s%20large-scale%20structures%20and%20disruptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20gathers%20disparate%20threads%20together%20meaningfully%2C%20allowing%20us%20to%20recognise%20key%20changes%20and%20see%20our%20present%20moment%20anew%3A%20a%20time%20when%2C%20he%20suggests%2C%20technology%20is%20trusted%20but%20science%20is%20not%20and%20emotion%20and%20individuality%20have%20superseded%20rationality%20and%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20are%20worries%20with%20this%20broad-brush%20approach.%20A%20focus%20on%20the%20differences%20across%20generations%20and%20centuries%20can%20obscure%20the%20continuities.%20It%20can%20also%20simplify.%20After%20all%2C%20in%20every%20era%2C%20there%20are%20dissenting%20voices%20and%20rival%20movements.%20Modern%20societies%20%E2%80%93%20like%2C%20perhaps%2C%20all%20societies%20%E2%80%93%20have%20threads%20of%20rationality%20and%20irrationality%2C%20domains%20where%20emotion%20is%20praised%20and%20times%20when%20it%20is%20repressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20a%20very%20different%20story%20of%20modernity%20could%20be%20told%2C%20arguing%20modernity%20actually%20represents%20the%20dawning%20awareness%20we%20must%20%3Cem%3Erelinquish%3C%2Fem%3E%20control%20and%20%3Cem%3Edivide%3C%2Fem%3E%20power.%20After%20all%2C%20modernity%20gave%20us%20the%20toleration%20valourised%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplato.stanford.edu%2Fentries%2Flocke%2F%5C%22%3ELocke%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplato.stanford.edu%2Fentries%2Fvoltaire%2F%5C%22%3EVoltaire%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20distrust%20of%20government%20that%20delivered%20the%20US%20Constitution.%20The%20elaboration%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D2856877%5C%22%3Eseparation%20of%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20democratic%20accountability.%20John%20Stuart%20Mill%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FOn_Liberty%5C%22%3Ecelebration%20of%20human%20diversity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20the%20creation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2015%2Fsep%2F07%2Fwhat-has-the-un-achieved-united-nations%5C%22%3Einstitutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20(such%20as%20the%20United%20Nations)%2C%20developed%20not%20to%20build%20heaven%20on%20earth%2C%20but%20merely%20to%20save%20us%20from%20hell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20sweeping%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bordoni%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9Cethical%20violence%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20recurring%20theme%20rather%20than%20a%20singular%20focus.%20He%20engages%20in%20many%20intriguing%20discussions.%20It%20is%20impossible%20in%20a%20review%20to%20even%20mention%20the%20myriad%20ideas%20he%20raises.%20Indeed%2C%20in%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20final%20chapter%2C%20the%20topic%20of%20ethical%20violence%20is%20entirely%20left%20behind%2C%20as%20Bordoni%20ruminates%20on%20technology%2C%20science%2C%20rationality%2C%20human%20individuality%2C%20loneliness%20and%20alienation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%3Cem%3EEthical%20Violence%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20valuable%20book%20for%20those%20who%20want%20their%20thinking%20to%20be%20challenged%20and%20enriched%2C%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20modern%20condition%2C%20and%20to%20consider%20where%20we%20might%20all%20be%20heading.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F220221%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fhugh-breakey-12916%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHugh%20Breakey%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20Deputy%20Director%2C%20Institute%20for%20Ethics%2C%20Governance%20%26amp%3B%20Law.%20President%2C%20Australian%20Association%20for%20Professional%20%26amp%3B%20Applied%20Ethics.%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fgriffith-university-828%5C%22%3EGriffith%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eunder%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2